6
00:00:49,752 --> 00:00:52,522
(Camping to change the mood for the kids)

7
00:00:52,992 --> 00:00:54,522
(What do you want to become, Hyo Min?)

8
00:00:54,892 --> 00:00:57,362
(Becoming an actor is one of my options!)

9
00:00:58,462 --> 00:01:01,102
(A new dream sparked by the acting class)

10
00:01:01,832 --> 00:01:04,072
(The kids' camp confession)

11
00:01:04,602 --> 00:01:06,472
(I love you, teachers.)

12
00:01:07,342 --> 00:01:10,242
(Nobody knew how the kids truly felt.)

13
00:01:11,172 --> 00:01:15,612
(The more time they spent together, the closer they got.)

14
00:01:17,012 --> 00:01:21,222
(After the evening that they opened their hearts to each other)

15
00:01:22,952 --> 00:01:25,322
(The next morning)

16
00:01:26,362 --> 00:01:28,192
(Hi!)

17
00:01:29,832 --> 00:01:32,162
(Won Jin is the 1st to arrive at school again.)

18
00:01:32,302 --> 00:01:33,401
(Lion)

19
00:01:33,402 --> 00:01:35,331
(What is he showing off first thing?)

20
00:01:35,332 --> 00:01:36,332
What is that?

21
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,202
Ju Eun gave it to me.

22
00:01:38,802 --> 00:01:40,902
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

23
00:01:42,672 --> 00:01:43,912
It's the Wizard.

24
00:01:44,072 --> 00:01:45,541
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

25
00:01:45,542 --> 00:01:46,612
(Customer satisfaction is at 100 percent.)

26
00:01:47,912 --> 00:01:50,952
(Ju Eun gifted drawings of "The Wizard of Oz" characters.)

27
00:01:51,312 --> 00:01:52,852
Can we make it after practice?

28
00:01:53,152 --> 00:01:54,451
- I'm in.
- Not me.

29
00:01:54,452 --> 00:01:55,452
I'm fine with it.

30
00:01:56,392 --> 00:01:57,892
I'm getting goosebumps.

31
00:01:58,322 --> 00:02:00,162
I'm really proud of her.

32
00:02:00,822 --> 00:02:01,861
Just how...

33
00:02:01,862 --> 00:02:02,862
(A model student who asks extraordinary questions)

34
00:02:03,062 --> 00:02:04,492
Do you have something to tell me?

35
00:02:04,562 --> 00:02:06,032
Please comfort the others.

36
00:02:06,332 --> 00:02:07,902
Okay, I'll comfort the others.

37
00:02:08,262 --> 00:02:10,102
Cry. Cry as much as you want.

38
00:02:10,472 --> 00:02:11,832
Cry until you get all puffy.

39
00:02:13,072 --> 00:02:16,812
(Lee Ju Eun, the acting class's light and salt)

40
00:02:17,172 --> 00:02:19,241
With courage, the Lion

41
00:02:19,242 --> 00:02:20,881
What was it? Returns?

42
00:02:20,882 --> 00:02:23,011
The Lion returns

43
00:02:23,012 --> 00:02:24,712
- Lends a hand.
- Here.

44
00:02:24,852 --> 00:02:26,882
- Let's draw the poster.
- Okay.

45
00:02:28,022 --> 00:02:29,592
Are we going to copy Eun Soo's poster?

46
00:02:29,822 --> 00:02:30,851
Yes.

47
00:02:30,852 --> 00:02:32,362
Let's copy hers.

48
00:02:33,522 --> 00:02:35,161
She drew it really well.

49
00:02:35,162 --> 00:02:37,032
- Right? The details are amazing.
- Yes.

50
00:02:37,262 --> 00:02:39,032
I can tell she draws at home.

51
00:02:39,062 --> 00:02:40,102
She must draw every day.

52
00:02:40,362 --> 00:02:44,131
Why don't we each draw a poster first?

53
00:02:44,132 --> 00:02:45,642
- Okay.
- We'll draw one each...

54
00:02:46,102 --> 00:02:48,671
and choose which one we like the most.

55
00:02:48,672 --> 00:02:49,842
Okay.

56
00:02:51,512 --> 00:02:53,181
(With courage, the Lion lends a hand)

57
00:02:53,182 --> 00:02:54,981
(With courage, the Lion returns)

58
00:02:54,982 --> 00:02:56,581
(Laughing)

59
00:02:56,582 --> 00:02:57,952
The Scarecrow

60
00:02:58,182 --> 00:03:02,191
(The Scarecrow's wisdom is so grand)

61
00:03:02,192 --> 00:03:03,891
(The Scarecrow's wisdom is so dark)

62
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,462
(Grand)

63
00:03:06,322 --> 00:03:10,231
(The Tin Man's heart is warm and true)

64
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:12,161
(Me and you)

65
00:03:12,162 --> 00:03:13,601
(Let's live)

66
00:03:13,602 --> 00:03:14,862
(Together)

67
00:03:15,702 --> 00:03:18,172
(While singing a mysterious working song)

68
00:03:19,072 --> 00:03:20,372
You're good at drawing.

69
00:03:20,702 --> 00:03:22,072
- Not bad, right?
- Yes.

70
00:03:22,442 --> 00:03:23,712
You're good, Tae Ri.

71
00:03:25,242 --> 00:03:27,082
But I like Kangnam's.

72
00:03:27,242 --> 00:03:28,442
Mine looks bad.

73
00:03:30,082 --> 00:03:32,652
(November 11 at Yongheung Elementary School)

74
00:03:33,522 --> 00:03:34,522
That?

75
00:03:34,752 --> 00:03:36,252
"That?"

76
00:03:36,552 --> 00:03:37,652
Seriously?

77
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:39,592
How could you say "that?"

78
00:03:40,422 --> 00:03:42,132
- "That?" - For real?

79
00:03:42,232 --> 00:03:43,332
Hold on.

80
00:03:43,992 --> 00:03:46,031
- What's wrong with it?
- Everyone has different taste.

81
00:03:46,032 --> 00:03:47,632
But to say "that?"

82
00:03:47,832 --> 00:03:49,172
Show me yours.

83
00:03:49,832 --> 00:03:51,131
- Mine's bad.
- Show me.

84
00:03:51,132 --> 00:03:53,471
(Yongheung Elementary School School Arts Festival)

85
00:03:53,472 --> 00:03:55,302
(Acting Class on November 11)

86
00:03:56,042 --> 00:03:57,142
What in the world?

87
00:04:00,382 --> 00:04:03,012
(Nip and tuck)

88
00:04:04,052 --> 00:04:05,252
You're good.

89
00:04:05,652 --> 00:04:07,382
- What do you think?
- It's so cute.

90
00:04:07,682 --> 00:04:09,492
The shadow effect is really nice.

91
00:04:09,652 --> 00:04:10,821
- This one?
- This one.

92
00:04:10,822 --> 00:04:12,221
This one. Here.

93
00:04:12,222 --> 00:04:13,961
(All entries have been submitted.)

94
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:16,031
(Mushroom House Poster Contest)

95
00:04:16,032 --> 00:04:18,832
- We drew these.
- We did.

96
00:04:19,202 --> 00:04:20,232
Okay.

97
00:04:20,902 --> 00:04:21,961
Out of...

98
00:04:21,962 --> 00:04:23,271
("That" by North Pole)

99
00:04:23,272 --> 00:04:24,671
the three entries,

100
00:04:24,672 --> 00:04:26,242
("What in the World?" by Potato, "Good One" by Tae Ri)

101
00:04:26,642 --> 00:04:27,901
this one won.

102
00:04:27,902 --> 00:04:29,411
(As expected, "Good One" won.)

103
00:04:29,412 --> 00:04:31,311
I prefer "Yonghoong Elementary School."

104
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,782
"Yonghoong Elementary School."

105
00:04:32,982 --> 00:04:34,111
Yonghoong Elementary School.

106
00:04:34,112 --> 00:04:35,481
- Yonghoong Elementary School.
- "Yonghoong Elementary School."

107
00:04:35,482 --> 00:04:36,752
- Yonghoong Elementary School.
- Yes.

108
00:04:37,052 --> 00:04:40,952
It's a marketing technique that makes you curious.

109
00:04:41,082 --> 00:04:43,321
(Teacher North Pole's Yonghoong is eliminated.)

110
00:04:43,322 --> 00:04:44,752
Should we color it in?

111
00:04:47,622 --> 00:04:50,392
(Coloring in the chosen poster)

112
00:04:51,662 --> 00:04:52,761
(Thanks to Eun Soo)

113
00:04:52,762 --> 00:04:53,831
(After crediting the source)

114
00:04:53,832 --> 00:04:55,501
This should be fine, right?

115
00:04:55,502 --> 00:04:57,531
- Yes, well done.
- Good job.

116
00:04:57,532 --> 00:05:00,102
(The poster is complete!)

117
00:05:00,372 --> 00:05:02,412
- I'll take the poster...
- Yes?

118
00:05:02,572 --> 00:05:03,912
- and make copies.
- Okay.

119
00:05:04,542 --> 00:05:07,482
- Okay?
- Nice.

120
00:05:08,582 --> 00:05:09,612
All right.

121
00:05:10,582 --> 00:05:12,552
I'll head out after a short break.

122
00:05:13,752 --> 00:05:15,251
(Relaxed)

123
00:05:15,252 --> 00:05:18,622
With courage, the Lion returns

124
00:05:19,122 --> 00:05:20,822
- The air is so refreshing.
- Right?

125
00:05:21,422 --> 00:05:22,491
What's this?

126
00:05:22,492 --> 00:05:24,192
- It feels like Hawaii.
- The kids are blowing bubbles.

127
00:05:24,692 --> 00:05:25,702
What?

128
00:05:26,632 --> 00:05:28,061
(And the kids' voices)

129
00:05:28,062 --> 00:05:29,602
Where? Oh, my.

130
00:05:32,102 --> 00:05:33,772
One, two, three.

131
00:05:42,482 --> 00:05:43,552
I see Kyung Mo.

132
00:05:43,912 --> 00:05:49,222
(Special moments found only here)

133
00:05:52,152 --> 00:05:55,522
(Listening to the kids' voices like a lullaby,)

134
00:05:57,032 --> 00:06:00,262
(North Pole Teacher has passed out.)

135
00:06:01,902 --> 00:06:04,172
(Blinking)

136
00:06:04,902 --> 00:06:07,802
(Getting up)

137
00:06:09,912 --> 00:06:11,511
(Feeling drowsy, he forgot about his task for a moment.)

138
00:06:11,512 --> 00:06:13,712
- I'm off.
- Okay, take care.

139
00:06:14,112 --> 00:06:15,311
- The poster.
- Right.

140
00:06:15,312 --> 00:06:16,511
And the costumes.

141
00:06:16,512 --> 00:06:18,451
The costumes we left to get tailored.

142
00:06:18,452 --> 00:06:19,482
Okay.

143
00:06:20,452 --> 00:06:21,921
The elementary students...

144
00:06:21,922 --> 00:06:23,391
will perform a play.

145
00:06:23,392 --> 00:06:27,522
We need to make costumes for it. I brought fabrics with me.

146
00:06:28,022 --> 00:06:29,191
Can you make it with this?

147
00:06:29,192 --> 00:06:30,762
This is for the Lion.

148
00:06:30,892 --> 00:06:32,261
This is for a puppy.

149
00:06:32,262 --> 00:06:33,361
- It's a skirt.
- Okay.

150
00:06:33,362 --> 00:06:35,102
- We need a bow.
- Okay.

151
00:06:36,002 --> 00:06:37,872
- This is for the Witch.
- Okay.

152
00:06:38,332 --> 00:06:40,342
It's like a hat that's on fire.

153
00:06:40,802 --> 00:06:42,201
- In a blaze.
- Like this?

154
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:43,742
- In a blaze.
- Got it.

155
00:06:43,942 --> 00:06:45,572
The Witch can throw fire.

156
00:06:46,312 --> 00:06:47,941
She has the power to do it.

157
00:06:47,942 --> 00:06:50,251
- I'll make them pretty.
- Make them the prettiest.

158
00:06:50,252 --> 00:06:51,952
- I'll make them the prettiest.
- The prettiest.

159
00:06:54,022 --> 00:06:57,622
(Did the costumes turn out the prettiest?)

160
00:06:58,652 --> 00:06:59,762
Hi.

161
00:07:00,292 --> 00:07:01,922
- Kangnam.
- Yes.

162
00:07:02,362 --> 00:07:03,832
Thanks, Kangnam.

163
00:07:04,032 --> 00:07:05,901
- Leave them over here.
- Okay.

164
00:07:05,902 --> 00:07:07,302
(Breathing heavily)

165
00:07:08,432 --> 00:07:10,301
(Kangnam is breathing heavily.)

166
00:07:10,302 --> 00:07:11,801
- Have some coffee.
- Have a sip of coffee.

167
00:07:11,802 --> 00:07:12,972
- Thank you.
- Oh, dear.

168
00:07:13,442 --> 00:07:15,842
Chug.

169
00:07:16,542 --> 00:07:18,811
Faster. Caffeine.

170
00:07:18,812 --> 00:07:20,042
(The coffee makes his eyes turn.)

171
00:07:20,512 --> 00:07:21,681
That hits the spot.

172
00:07:21,682 --> 00:07:23,281
- Let's look at the costumes.
- That hits the spot.

173
00:07:23,282 --> 00:07:25,512
(Unboxing the long-awaited costumes)

174
00:07:27,152 --> 00:07:28,152
Wicked Witch of the West?

175
00:07:28,152 --> 00:07:29,152
- Yes, Wicked Witch of the West.
- Wicked Witch of the West.

176
00:07:29,153 --> 00:07:30,451
The Wizard. No, the Gatekeeper.

177
00:07:30,452 --> 00:07:31,521
- The Gatekeeper.
- The Wizard?

178
00:07:31,522 --> 00:07:32,962
No, it's the Wizard.

179
00:07:33,462 --> 00:07:36,292
- It's prettier than I imagined.
- Right?

180
00:07:36,492 --> 00:07:38,462
Take a look. I'm sure you'll be surprised.

181
00:07:38,562 --> 00:07:39,732
Is that for the Lion?

182
00:07:40,232 --> 00:07:41,401
- Toto.
- Toto.

183
00:07:41,402 --> 00:07:42,931
(And the costumes for the Lion and Toto)

184
00:07:42,932 --> 00:07:44,932
- The dressmaker is amazing.
- I told you.

185
00:07:45,072 --> 00:07:46,242
The kids will love it.

186
00:07:46,642 --> 00:07:49,071
- They absolutely will.
- It'll finally sink in.

187
00:07:49,072 --> 00:07:50,672
(The costumes and props are ready.)

188
00:07:51,072 --> 00:07:53,211
Today is the ninth class.

189
00:07:53,212 --> 00:07:55,011
(9th class)

190
00:07:55,012 --> 00:07:56,851
Wait for me. Walk slowly.

191
00:07:56,852 --> 00:08:00,452
(The young actors and actresses appear while humming.)

192
00:08:02,152 --> 00:08:03,291
(Holding the door open)

193
00:08:03,292 --> 00:08:04,451
- Give me a second.
- Hi.

194
00:08:04,452 --> 00:08:06,361
- Hi.
- Hi.

195
00:08:06,362 --> 00:08:08,321
- Hey.
- Hi.

196
00:08:08,322 --> 00:08:11,762
(The ninth class begins with enthusiasm.)

197
00:08:13,162 --> 00:08:14,902
Let's start with costumes today.

198
00:08:15,032 --> 00:08:16,231
The costumes are here. Guys,

199
00:08:16,232 --> 00:08:17,971
- a round of applause!
- A round of applause!

200
00:08:17,972 --> 00:08:19,201
(Cheering)

201
00:08:19,202 --> 00:08:20,971
Let's put the costumes on...

202
00:08:20,972 --> 00:08:24,171
and rehearse the whole thing, okay?

203
00:08:24,172 --> 00:08:25,172
- Okay.
- Okay.

204
00:08:25,173 --> 00:08:26,341
Good, then...

205
00:08:26,342 --> 00:08:27,381
Ju Eun and Eun Soo.

206
00:08:27,382 --> 00:08:29,111
- Come to me.
- Let's go.

207
00:08:29,112 --> 00:08:30,452
- Me!
- The Scarecrow.

208
00:08:30,512 --> 00:08:31,981
The Lion must be cool and strong,

209
00:08:31,982 --> 00:08:34,521
and so we even prepared this. Come here.

210
00:08:34,522 --> 00:08:36,091
A cape. Stay still.

211
00:08:36,092 --> 00:08:37,821
(Once the cape is on)

212
00:08:37,822 --> 00:08:39,522
You're looking cool all alone.

213
00:08:39,622 --> 00:08:40,661
(Majestic)

214
00:08:40,662 --> 00:08:42,062
Turn around.

215
00:08:43,462 --> 00:08:46,032
Ms. Kim, I've become a fashionista.

216
00:08:46,502 --> 00:08:47,502
Oh, my.

217
00:08:48,162 --> 00:08:49,232
North Pole Teacher!

218
00:08:49,932 --> 00:08:51,901
It's the other way around, North Pole Teacher.

219
00:08:51,902 --> 00:08:53,242
The zipper should be at the back.

220
00:08:53,772 --> 00:08:55,741
- The zipper should be at the back.
- Sorry.

221
00:08:55,742 --> 00:08:57,242
Help him get dressed again.

222
00:08:57,572 --> 00:08:59,942
Come on, North Pole Teacher.

223
00:09:00,412 --> 00:09:01,642
Help me wear it properly.

224
00:09:02,112 --> 00:09:03,582
Okay, I will. Here.

225
00:09:04,182 --> 00:09:05,951
- Your legs.
- Take my shoes off first.

226
00:09:05,952 --> 00:09:07,822
Are your legs in? Try it on.

227
00:09:08,182 --> 00:09:10,521
I need to take my legs out first.

228
00:09:10,522 --> 00:09:11,652
Why? Do you need to take them off first?

229
00:09:12,222 --> 00:09:13,861
- Oh, right.
- Of course,

230
00:09:13,862 --> 00:09:15,662
because it's the other way around.

231
00:09:15,932 --> 00:09:16,932
Hold on.

232
00:09:17,562 --> 00:09:18,562
Tae Ri.

233
00:09:18,932 --> 00:09:20,001
(Exploding with chemistry)

234
00:09:20,002 --> 00:09:21,361
Shouldn't this go to the back?

235
00:09:21,362 --> 00:09:22,732
Ms. Kim!

236
00:09:23,032 --> 00:09:25,102
Ha Yun, the teachers made this.

237
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:26,841
- The wand.
- Face me.

238
00:09:26,842 --> 00:09:28,202
Don't play baseball with it, okay?

239
00:09:28,772 --> 00:09:29,812
Come here.

240
00:09:30,042 --> 00:09:32,442
(Gifting the handmade wand to the Wizard)

241
00:09:33,682 --> 00:09:35,081
Come out once you're all dressed.

242
00:09:35,082 --> 00:09:37,352
(Perfect for playing baseball with)

243
00:09:38,012 --> 00:09:39,251
Are you done, Toto?

244
00:09:39,252 --> 00:09:40,651
My tail is right here.

245
00:09:40,652 --> 00:09:42,022
It's right there. How cute.

246
00:09:43,152 --> 00:09:44,521
You look cute. It suits you.

247
00:09:44,522 --> 00:09:45,891
Let's go!

248
00:09:45,892 --> 00:09:46,992
(Toto is excited to have a tail.)

249
00:09:47,222 --> 00:09:48,861
- Come here.
- Come out once you're all dressed.

250
00:09:48,862 --> 00:09:49,892
Okay.

251
00:09:50,062 --> 00:09:51,561
Hi, Lion.

252
00:09:51,562 --> 00:09:52,761
- Hi.
- It looks good on you.

253
00:09:52,762 --> 00:09:53,832
Hi.

254
00:09:55,602 --> 00:09:58,002
(North Pole Teacher is in charge of Dorothy's ribbon even today.)

255
00:09:58,332 --> 00:09:59,572
How's the ribbon?

256
00:10:00,502 --> 00:10:02,572
- I want to see myself in a mirror.
- Do you need a mirror?

257
00:10:02,812 --> 00:10:04,171
Look here.

258
00:10:04,172 --> 00:10:05,672
(Here's a mirror.)

259
00:10:06,742 --> 00:10:08,042
(Impressed)

260
00:10:08,142 --> 00:10:09,482
- Not bad, right?
- Yes.

261
00:10:10,152 --> 00:10:11,351
- Nice, right?
- Yes.

262
00:10:11,352 --> 00:10:13,182
You became the real Dorothy.

263
00:10:13,682 --> 00:10:15,022
Dorothy looks really happy.

264
00:10:16,192 --> 00:10:17,752
You're all sparkly.

265
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,052
It suits you.

266
00:10:19,692 --> 00:10:21,121
- Hi, Scarecrow.
- Hi.

267
00:10:21,122 --> 00:10:22,122
You are the Scarecrow.

268
00:10:22,492 --> 00:10:24,991
Ju Eun, don't forget the Munchkin's hat.

269
00:10:24,992 --> 00:10:26,261
If it were summer...

270
00:10:26,262 --> 00:10:27,731
Hi, I'm the Munchkin.

271
00:10:27,732 --> 00:10:28,732
(Everyone is all dressed up.)

272
00:10:29,632 --> 00:10:31,701
Guys, don't you miss Mr. CO KUN?

273
00:10:31,702 --> 00:10:32,741
- We do!
- We do!

274
00:10:32,742 --> 00:10:36,011
Mr. CO KUN sent us a few songs.

275
00:10:36,012 --> 00:10:38,842
We're going to listen to them together.

276
00:10:39,072 --> 00:10:41,111
Remember us stomping our feet and clapping our hands?

277
00:10:41,112 --> 00:10:42,141
- Yes.
- Yes.

278
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:44,251
Those sounds are included in the songs.

279
00:10:44,252 --> 00:10:45,351
- It's a cheerful song.
- A cheerful song.

280
00:10:45,352 --> 00:10:46,652
A cheerful song.

281
00:10:47,982 --> 00:10:50,122
(The previous traveling song...)

282
00:10:50,992 --> 00:10:53,692
(only had a melody without any drum sounds.)

283
00:10:53,862 --> 00:10:55,492
Okay, let's begin.

284
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:57,292
In 1, 2, 3.

285
00:11:00,162 --> 00:11:04,372
(Adding in the stomps recorded with the kids,)

286
00:11:05,972 --> 00:11:08,842
(a cheerful traveling song has been born!)

287
00:11:09,712 --> 00:11:12,341
(Amazed)

288
00:11:12,342 --> 00:11:13,411
The next song is...

289
00:11:13,412 --> 00:11:16,711
Mr. CO KUN made a song for when Dorothy lands...

290
00:11:16,712 --> 00:11:18,211
in the new world.

291
00:11:18,212 --> 00:11:19,322
Let's listen to it, shall we?

292
00:11:20,582 --> 00:11:21,852
Listen carefully.

293
00:11:23,552 --> 00:11:25,321
(Listening to it quietly)

294
00:11:25,322 --> 00:11:27,162
You'll hear a creaking sound. Focus.

295
00:11:28,862 --> 00:11:31,762
(The music once the door to Oz opens)

296
00:11:32,462 --> 00:11:33,632
Our voices.

297
00:11:33,832 --> 00:11:36,032
- It's what we recorded.
- Bow wow.

298
00:11:41,002 --> 00:11:42,371
(It's my voice.)

299
00:11:42,372 --> 00:11:43,711
It was made with our voices.

300
00:11:43,712 --> 00:11:46,811
(The music is all the more special because it was made together.)

301
00:11:46,812 --> 00:11:49,212
Next is the scene when the Lion appears.

302
00:11:49,312 --> 00:11:50,711
- When the Lion appears.
- Remember...

303
00:11:50,712 --> 00:11:52,481
what kind of music plays when the Lion appears?

304
00:11:52,482 --> 00:11:54,751
- Spooky music, right?
- Spooky music.

305
00:11:54,752 --> 00:11:55,921
Play the music.

306
00:11:55,922 --> 00:11:57,152
(A spooky music for the Lion)

307
00:12:00,462 --> 00:12:02,522
- Loudly.
- It's when her friends appear.

308
00:12:03,492 --> 00:12:05,732
- Really.
- This is like a horror movie.

309
00:12:06,032 --> 00:12:07,032
Wait.

310
00:12:07,602 --> 00:12:08,862
- The music is...
- Oh, dear.

311
00:12:10,202 --> 00:12:11,431
(Lion and Dorothy's party)

312
00:12:11,432 --> 00:12:13,402
Toto. Focus, Toto.

313
00:12:13,902 --> 00:12:16,141
(Fully immersed thanks to the music)

314
00:12:16,142 --> 00:12:17,241
Won Jin,

315
00:12:17,242 --> 00:12:18,741
- appear with a loud roar...
- Roar!

316
00:12:18,742 --> 00:12:21,141
when the music ends, okay?

317
00:12:21,142 --> 00:12:22,241
You must roar.

318
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:25,151
The music is really spooky that it's scary.

319
00:12:25,152 --> 00:12:27,751
The sounds are like those from a haunted house.

320
00:12:27,752 --> 00:12:29,392
- The Witch.
- The Witch appears.

321
00:12:29,922 --> 00:12:31,022
The cape.

322
00:12:31,552 --> 00:12:33,992
You must run as if you're escaping from a haunted house.

323
00:12:34,922 --> 00:12:36,332
(Nervous)

324
00:12:36,592 --> 00:12:37,592
(Laughing)

325
00:12:37,593 --> 00:12:39,401
(The Witch's laughter echoes.)

326
00:12:39,402 --> 00:12:40,732
(Laughing)

327
00:12:40,832 --> 00:12:42,432
(The owner of the laughter)

328
00:12:42,702 --> 00:12:44,332
(Laughing)

329
00:12:44,432 --> 00:12:46,342
What should you be doing?

330
00:12:47,342 --> 00:12:48,602
The Wicked Witch of the West has appeared.

331
00:12:49,202 --> 00:12:50,511
You can do it, right?

332
00:12:50,512 --> 00:12:51,812
- Yes.
- You can act startled, right?

333
00:12:52,312 --> 00:12:53,442
(Like this?)

334
00:12:53,812 --> 00:12:55,212
(Laughing)

335
00:12:55,282 --> 00:12:58,312
Mr. CO KUN gave us four songs as presents.

336
00:12:58,482 --> 00:12:59,482
Awesome, right?

337
00:12:59,483 --> 00:13:02,722
- Give it up for Mr. CO KUN.
- Yes!

338
00:13:03,052 --> 00:13:04,522
I love it.

339
00:13:04,622 --> 00:13:06,062
I especially like the theme song for the Witch.

340
00:13:06,322 --> 00:13:07,462
The Witch's theme song?

341
00:13:07,722 --> 00:13:10,132
(Encore)

342
00:13:10,592 --> 00:13:13,561
Now, we're going to have a run-through.

343
00:13:13,562 --> 00:13:15,032
What's a run-through?

344
00:13:15,662 --> 00:13:17,231
- From start to finish.
- From start to finish.

345
00:13:17,232 --> 00:13:18,701
A run-through is going over the performance...

346
00:13:18,702 --> 00:13:20,202
from start to finish.

347
00:13:20,302 --> 00:13:23,411
I want you to practice in the meantime, okay?

348
00:13:23,412 --> 00:13:26,541
The actual run-through begins in 15 minutes, all right?

349
00:13:26,542 --> 00:13:28,411
- Yes!
- Yes!

350
00:13:28,412 --> 00:13:29,412
(The run-through will start after a short practice.)

351
00:13:29,452 --> 00:13:31,652
- Rehearse with me.
- Sure.

352
00:13:32,452 --> 00:13:33,522
Did you memorize all the lines?

353
00:13:33,822 --> 00:13:36,121
You guys are really kind.

354
00:13:36,122 --> 00:13:37,222
- Now...
- You need to slow down.

355
00:13:37,522 --> 00:13:38,652
- You...
- Start.

356
00:13:38,752 --> 00:13:41,862
You guys are really kind.

357
00:13:42,192 --> 00:13:43,961
- I want a heart...
- A warm heart.

358
00:13:43,962 --> 00:13:46,802
I want a warm heart.

359
00:13:47,162 --> 00:13:50,271
Now, Toto. "We can do it."

360
00:13:50,272 --> 00:13:52,072
We can do it!

361
00:13:52,902 --> 00:13:53,942
Is that his loudest?

362
00:13:54,602 --> 00:13:56,442
Kyung Mo, why don't you raise your voice a bit more?

363
00:13:56,542 --> 00:13:57,711
Good. Begin.

364
00:13:57,712 --> 00:14:00,281
- We can do it.
- A little louder!

365
00:14:00,282 --> 00:14:01,282
- Start.
- We can do it!

366
00:14:01,283 --> 00:14:02,751
Just a little louder!

367
00:14:02,752 --> 00:14:05,111
We can do it!

368
00:14:05,112 --> 00:14:06,622
That's how loud I want you to be.

369
00:14:06,882 --> 00:14:08,252
- Okay.
- That's good.

370
00:14:08,352 --> 00:14:09,892
You listen when your brother tells you.

371
00:14:09,992 --> 00:14:11,492
You never listen to me.

372
00:14:12,252 --> 00:14:13,292
That's disappointing.

373
00:14:14,122 --> 00:14:16,931
Let me know if you understand me.

374
00:14:16,932 --> 00:14:17,961
Okay.

375
00:14:17,962 --> 00:14:20,802
The Tin Man wanted a warm heart.

376
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:21,931
Did you understand that?

377
00:14:21,932 --> 00:14:22,932
- No.
- No, right?

378
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:25,171
They'll hear your voice from a distance.

379
00:14:25,172 --> 00:14:28,171
- Right.
- So, they might think,

380
00:14:28,172 --> 00:14:29,741
- "What is Ha Yun saying?" - Okay.

381
00:14:29,742 --> 00:14:32,841
- It's important to enunciate it.
- Guys.

382
00:14:32,842 --> 00:14:36,981
Guys, your wishes already came true.

383
00:14:36,982 --> 00:14:38,152
Say one word at a time.

384
00:14:38,252 --> 00:14:40,551
- What do you think will happen...
- What do you think will happen...

385
00:14:40,552 --> 00:14:42,321
- to Dorothy and her friends?
- to Dorothy and her friends?

386
00:14:42,322 --> 00:14:46,052
Then, swish. Now, open up...

387
00:14:46,162 --> 00:14:48,362
and shout, "Ha!"

388
00:14:48,462 --> 00:14:50,261
- "Ha!" - There you go.

389
00:14:50,262 --> 00:14:53,201
And your friends will be scared.

390
00:14:53,202 --> 00:14:55,332
That's when you say your line.

391
00:14:55,662 --> 00:14:57,571
Samsung's Kim Ji Chan

392
00:14:57,572 --> 00:14:59,441
- Hit a single - Hit a single

393
00:14:59,442 --> 00:15:01,271
- Samsung's Kim Ji Chan - Samsung's Kim Ji Chan

394
00:15:01,272 --> 00:15:03,041
- Chan, Chan, Chan, Kim Ji Chan - Chan, Chan, Chan, Kim Ji Chan

395
00:15:03,042 --> 00:15:05,172
Chan, Chan, Chan, Kim Ji Chan

396
00:15:05,272 --> 00:15:07,112
Samsung's Kim Ji Chan

397
00:15:08,182 --> 00:15:09,882
Are you a Samsung Lions fan?

398
00:15:10,552 --> 00:15:12,182
No, I'm a Lotte Giants fan.

399
00:15:12,922 --> 00:15:14,322
Why do you like Lotte?

400
00:15:14,722 --> 00:15:17,952
Me? Because Lotte's chocolates taste good.

401
00:15:18,952 --> 00:15:21,092
But that team is based in Seoul.

402
00:15:23,592 --> 00:15:25,032
We should practice.

403
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:26,632
We should.

404
00:15:26,732 --> 00:15:28,362
- Come on.
- Let's start practicing.

405
00:15:30,172 --> 00:15:32,431
Say your last line, "What's your wish?"

406
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:33,641
I'll say Dorothy's lines.

407
00:15:33,642 --> 00:15:35,172
What's your wish?

408
00:15:35,272 --> 00:15:36,572
You don't know that?

409
00:15:37,842 --> 00:15:39,741
I don't know anything...

410
00:15:39,742 --> 00:15:43,112
because I'm made of straws.

411
00:15:43,582 --> 00:15:45,652
I know nothing.

412
00:15:46,922 --> 00:15:47,981
- Hyo Min.
- Yes?

413
00:15:47,982 --> 00:15:50,591
Is that how you're going to perform in front of an audience?

414
00:15:50,592 --> 00:15:51,751
- No.
- Is it?

415
00:15:51,752 --> 00:15:53,161
- No.
- You need to be...

416
00:15:53,162 --> 00:15:55,122
energetic when you practice.

417
00:15:55,292 --> 00:15:56,661
Click.

418
00:15:56,662 --> 00:15:58,491
I need you to be loud, Hyo Min.

419
00:15:58,492 --> 00:15:59,802
Hyo Min, good luck today.

420
00:16:00,162 --> 00:16:02,561
Good luck. Take care of all the other kids.

421
00:16:02,562 --> 00:16:04,171
You were so cool yesterday.

422
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:06,872
- Okay.
- But say the lines a bit louder.

423
00:16:07,472 --> 00:16:09,372
Their costumes are good, but...

424
00:16:10,012 --> 00:16:11,272
Oh, it's the costume?

425
00:16:11,672 --> 00:16:12,672
A little.

426
00:16:13,282 --> 00:16:14,682
What do you want to do with yours?

427
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:16,481
How do you want it to be?

428
00:16:16,482 --> 00:16:18,182
- I...
- Yes, give us your opinion.

429
00:16:18,612 --> 00:16:22,021
This costume is a little hot.

430
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:23,451
- It's hot?
- Yes.

431
00:16:23,452 --> 00:16:25,191
- Do you want a cooler one?
- Yes.

432
00:16:25,192 --> 00:16:26,391
- Let me think about it.
- Okay.

433
00:16:26,392 --> 00:16:27,462
Will that make you feel better?

434
00:16:28,092 --> 00:16:29,092
All right.

435
00:16:29,932 --> 00:16:32,361
There's a thick forest ahead!

436
00:16:32,362 --> 00:16:34,502
It's too dangerous to go through.

437
00:16:34,832 --> 00:16:37,071
Yes, Tin Man, you should join us!

438
00:16:37,072 --> 00:16:39,071
Your friends are in front of you, right?

439
00:16:39,072 --> 00:16:40,802
So, you picture all those people...

440
00:16:40,902 --> 00:16:42,142
as you say the lines.

441
00:16:42,742 --> 00:16:44,542
Loud and clear.

442
00:16:45,842 --> 00:16:48,641
Kids, to your positions!

443
00:16:48,642 --> 00:16:49,711
(Getting ready for the run-through)

444
00:16:49,712 --> 00:16:50,712
- Ha Yun, - Yes?

445
00:16:50,713 --> 00:16:52,482
- say the words clearly, okay?
- Okay.

446
00:16:53,052 --> 00:16:54,151
- Let's give it a go.
- Yes.

447
00:16:54,152 --> 00:16:55,482
- Good luck.
- Good luck!

448
00:16:55,582 --> 00:16:56,991
(How will their first run-through go?)

449
00:16:56,992 --> 00:16:57,992
Let's start.

450
00:16:58,692 --> 00:16:59,792
The camera's rolling.

451
00:17:00,522 --> 00:17:01,921
(Nervous)

452
00:17:01,922 --> 00:17:03,332
Start!

453
00:17:03,432 --> 00:17:05,732
(The run-through begins.)

454
00:17:06,332 --> 00:17:07,332
(The play starts with a narration.)

455
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,771
Dorothy, a girl living in Mungyeong,

456
00:17:09,772 --> 00:17:13,101
ended up in the strange and wondrous Land of Oz...

457
00:17:13,102 --> 00:17:14,771
with her dog Toto,

458
00:17:14,772 --> 00:17:17,842
as a whirlwind swept her house away.

459
00:17:18,242 --> 00:17:20,941
- Boom.
- The curtain opens.

460
00:17:20,942 --> 00:17:22,042
(Number 1, Dorothy's scene)

461
00:17:22,142 --> 00:17:23,981
Cue music.

462
00:17:23,982 --> 00:17:26,282
(Dorothy's song plays.)

463
00:17:27,882 --> 00:17:28,922
Wait for it.

464
00:17:30,922 --> 00:17:36,192
(Dorothy opens the door and enters the stage.)

465
00:17:38,462 --> 00:17:39,732
Kyung Mo, stay back.

466
00:17:40,932 --> 00:17:43,802
(Because it's Dorothy's time right now.)

467
00:17:44,302 --> 00:17:46,132
(So cute)

468
00:17:47,872 --> 00:17:51,812
(Toto opens the door and follows her.)

469
00:17:55,912 --> 00:17:58,382
Goodness, this isn't Mungyeong!

470
00:17:58,682 --> 00:18:01,082
It's so brilliant and colorful!

471
00:18:01,922 --> 00:18:05,551
(Toto: It's dazzling! Dorothy: It's dazzling!)

472
00:18:05,552 --> 00:18:06,592
"It's dazzling."

473
00:18:10,092 --> 00:18:11,432
It's dazzling!

474
00:18:11,892 --> 00:18:15,162
- Sniff, sniff. I smell flowers.
- Sniff, sniff. I smell flowers.

475
00:18:15,902 --> 00:18:17,732
(Good save, Eun Soo.)

476
00:18:18,002 --> 00:18:20,502
- I'm speaking!
- Toto is speaking!

477
00:18:28,082 --> 00:18:29,882
(Gently putting them down)

478
00:18:30,352 --> 00:18:33,151
Here, wear these shoes. They belong to the Witch.

479
00:18:33,152 --> 00:18:35,182
(The silver shoes should have been there from the start.)

480
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:37,621
She was wearing the shoes.

481
00:18:37,622 --> 00:18:40,092
(She was wearing them.)

482
00:18:42,362 --> 00:18:44,932
Where are you from, Wizard?

483
00:18:45,032 --> 00:18:46,732
- She's good.
- I'm not a wizard.

484
00:18:47,062 --> 00:18:48,432
My name is Dorothy.

485
00:18:48,532 --> 00:18:50,772
I want to go back home.

486
00:18:51,602 --> 00:18:55,272
Then, why don't you go and find the Wizard of Oz?

487
00:18:55,702 --> 00:18:57,171
Which way should I go?

488
00:18:57,172 --> 00:18:58,511
(Facial acting)

489
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,512
She's adorable.

490
00:19:00,782 --> 00:19:03,782
Here, wear these shoes. They belong to the Witch.

491
00:19:03,982 --> 00:19:07,682
And I'll give this cute puppy a bow tie.

492
00:19:07,882 --> 00:19:10,491
(He wears the tie, and he's ready to go.)

493
00:19:10,492 --> 00:19:11,922
Yes, you're thrilled.

494
00:19:12,952 --> 00:19:14,092
Come on, Toto!

495
00:19:14,462 --> 00:19:16,221
Let's go together!

496
00:19:16,222 --> 00:19:17,232
- Yes!
- Yes!

497
00:19:17,492 --> 00:19:18,492
Well done!

498
00:19:19,702 --> 00:19:20,732
They're doing it.

499
00:19:20,862 --> 00:19:22,402
Start!

500
00:19:24,132 --> 00:19:28,041
Stay excited!

501
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:30,111
The curtain closes!

502
00:19:30,112 --> 00:19:31,112
Kyung Mo!

503
00:19:31,612 --> 00:19:33,742
(Come back.)

504
00:19:34,182 --> 00:19:36,082
(Proud of her)

505
00:19:36,852 --> 00:19:39,952
(Number 2, Scarecrow's scene)

506
00:19:40,252 --> 00:19:44,952
They're not afraid of me anymore.

507
00:19:45,052 --> 00:19:46,362
(Be confident!)

508
00:19:46,622 --> 00:19:47,722
(Nodding)

509
00:19:49,422 --> 00:19:52,061
- Hi.
- Hi, the weather is lovely.

510
00:19:52,062 --> 00:19:55,032
Thanks for talking to me when even the crows ignore me.

511
00:19:55,262 --> 00:19:56,771
(Great!)

512
00:19:56,772 --> 00:19:58,371
I'll help you down!

513
00:19:58,372 --> 00:20:00,001
In 1, 2, 3.

514
00:20:00,002 --> 00:20:01,502
- Come on down!
- Come on down!

515
00:20:01,972 --> 00:20:06,212
Hi. I'm made of straws,

516
00:20:06,312 --> 00:20:09,212
so I don't even know who I am.

517
00:20:12,182 --> 00:20:13,282
Do I have more lines?

518
00:20:14,122 --> 00:20:15,521
(Nodding)

519
00:20:15,522 --> 00:20:16,621
"Could the Wizard of Oz..."

520
00:20:16,622 --> 00:20:21,321
Could the Wizard of Oz give me a brain?

521
00:20:21,322 --> 00:20:22,322
(He makes it through, thanks to Eun Soo.)

522
00:20:22,323 --> 00:20:23,732
Let's go and ask him together.

523
00:20:24,592 --> 00:20:28,561
The Wizard of Oz might grant...

524
00:20:28,562 --> 00:20:30,332
all our wishes.

525
00:20:31,502 --> 00:20:33,871
Should we hit the road?

526
00:20:33,872 --> 00:20:35,701
(The Scarecrow joins them.)

527
00:20:35,702 --> 00:20:38,712
(Making a mistake)

528
00:20:39,172 --> 00:20:42,782
(Scarecrow, be more confident.)

529
00:20:43,712 --> 00:20:47,452
(Number 3, Tin Man's scene)

530
00:20:48,782 --> 00:20:50,291
(They meet the Tin Man who's stuck.)

531
00:20:50,292 --> 00:20:51,292
Okay.

532
00:20:52,492 --> 00:20:54,322
- Grunt.
- Sniff, sniff.

533
00:20:54,422 --> 00:20:57,662
- Grunt.
- Sniff, sniff. I smell something!

534
00:20:58,292 --> 00:21:00,532
There's an oil can at my waist.

535
00:21:00,832 --> 00:21:03,032
Will you please oil my joints?

536
00:21:04,302 --> 00:21:06,702
(They quickly get into position.)

537
00:21:10,242 --> 00:21:12,912
(They work together and oil his joints.)

538
00:21:14,582 --> 00:21:16,952
(Adding a stretch)

539
00:21:17,682 --> 00:21:18,682
(Tin Man, the stretch was a good touch. Please keep doing it.)

540
00:21:18,683 --> 00:21:22,182
You guys are really kind.

541
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:26,022
I may look like I'm made of tin, but I used to be a human.

542
00:21:26,522 --> 00:21:28,791
The Wicked Witch of the West cursed me,

543
00:21:28,792 --> 00:21:32,032
and I turned into a heartless tin man.

544
00:21:32,132 --> 00:21:33,601
What? The Wicked Witch of the West?

545
00:21:33,602 --> 00:21:35,462
Before she comes...

546
00:21:35,762 --> 00:21:37,231
What? The Wicked Witch of the West?

547
00:21:37,232 --> 00:21:40,971
Before she comes, we're going to find the Wizard of Oz...

548
00:21:40,972 --> 00:21:42,802
and ask him to send us home.

549
00:21:42,902 --> 00:21:44,872
Tin Man, you should join us.

550
00:21:45,612 --> 00:21:46,642
- Yes!
- Yes!

551
00:21:48,182 --> 00:21:49,241
(They're about to leave, and...)

552
00:21:49,242 --> 00:21:50,312
- No!
- What?

553
00:21:51,082 --> 00:21:53,982
There's a thick forest ahead.

554
00:21:54,082 --> 00:21:57,792
It's too dangerous to go through.

555
00:21:58,152 --> 00:21:59,352
What should we do, then?

556
00:22:01,022 --> 00:22:03,232
(Her acting is getting better and better.)

557
00:22:03,862 --> 00:22:06,262
(Amazed)

558
00:22:06,432 --> 00:22:09,462
Though I don't have a heart, I know how to chop down trees.

559
00:22:11,602 --> 00:22:15,002
(The Tin Man cuts down trees for his friends.)

560
00:22:16,502 --> 00:22:18,612
- Yes!
- All right!

561
00:22:19,272 --> 00:22:20,342
Perfect.

562
00:22:21,742 --> 00:22:24,812
The others leave, and Toto comes to the center.

563
00:22:25,912 --> 00:22:27,352
The best!

564
00:22:30,022 --> 00:22:32,452
(The song for the Lion plays.)

565
00:22:32,752 --> 00:22:33,791
He's so cute.

566
00:22:33,792 --> 00:22:35,891
(Number 4, Lion's scene)

567
00:22:35,892 --> 00:22:37,432
(The Lion is hiding.)

568
00:22:37,662 --> 00:22:40,162
It's scary. Listen to the song.

569
00:22:43,032 --> 00:22:46,072
(Toto senses an eerie vibe.)

570
00:22:46,872 --> 00:22:48,902
Toto hears a roar.

571
00:22:49,002 --> 00:22:51,112
- Roar!
- Yelp!

572
00:22:53,042 --> 00:22:54,042
I like that.

573
00:22:54,043 --> 00:22:55,842
(Loving it)

574
00:22:55,982 --> 00:22:58,281
- Roar!
- Yelp!

575
00:22:58,282 --> 00:22:59,382
Toto!

576
00:23:00,582 --> 00:23:01,852
(Dorothy's punch)

577
00:23:02,682 --> 00:23:04,551
(Crying)

578
00:23:04,552 --> 00:23:06,022
He's crying.

579
00:23:06,522 --> 00:23:08,421
Stop bullying Toto!

580
00:23:08,422 --> 00:23:12,432
No matter how scary you are, I will protect Toto!

581
00:23:12,792 --> 00:23:13,832
Sorry.

582
00:23:13,962 --> 00:23:16,101
I was afraid of Toto.

583
00:23:16,102 --> 00:23:19,072
I was afraid because Toto roared at me.

584
00:23:19,432 --> 00:23:21,372
I'm actually a coward.

585
00:23:21,402 --> 00:23:24,441
We're on our way to find the Wizard of Oz.

586
00:23:24,442 --> 00:23:26,172
Why don't you come with us?

587
00:23:26,372 --> 00:23:28,512
He'll grant my wish?

588
00:23:28,742 --> 00:23:31,552
Will he be able to give me a brain...

589
00:23:32,552 --> 00:23:34,552
- He'll grant my wish?
- That's okay.

590
00:23:34,882 --> 00:23:37,622
Will he be able to give me courage, then?

591
00:23:38,392 --> 00:23:39,752
(Relieved)

592
00:23:39,922 --> 00:23:42,162
Let's go and find him!

593
00:23:42,962 --> 00:23:46,362
Okay. The curtain closes.

594
00:23:47,302 --> 00:23:48,302
(Great!)

595
00:23:48,303 --> 00:23:50,172
The journey was peaceful.

596
00:23:51,272 --> 00:23:54,241
(But the peaceful journey didn't last so long.)

597
00:23:54,242 --> 00:23:57,712
But...

598
00:23:57,742 --> 00:23:58,742
You've got this.

599
00:23:58,743 --> 00:24:01,241
But the peaceful journey didn't last so long.

600
00:24:01,242 --> 00:24:02,882
(Success)

601
00:24:03,412 --> 00:24:06,152
(Number 5, Wicked Witch of the West scene)

602
00:24:06,922 --> 00:24:10,052
(She turns from a narrator to the Wicked Witch of the West.)

603
00:24:12,692 --> 00:24:16,292
(The Wicked Witch of the West hides herself.)

604
00:24:16,562 --> 00:24:19,861
Sniff, sniff. I smell fire.

605
00:24:19,862 --> 00:24:23,232
What? Fire? It's going to burn all my straws!

606
00:24:25,202 --> 00:24:26,472
(The Wicked Witch of the West appears.)

607
00:24:26,872 --> 00:24:29,372
(Startled)

608
00:24:29,972 --> 00:24:31,742
(The Lion is scared.)

609
00:24:31,872 --> 00:24:34,582
Dorothy, we finally meet.

610
00:24:34,942 --> 00:24:38,382
I knew you'd go to the Wizard of Oz.

611
00:24:39,282 --> 00:24:41,452
Are you the Wicked Witch of the West?

612
00:24:42,052 --> 00:24:44,491
Yes, I'm the Wicked Witch of the West.

613
00:24:44,492 --> 00:24:45,592
(A well-matched act-off)

614
00:24:46,392 --> 00:24:48,492
How foolish you are.

615
00:24:48,522 --> 00:24:50,431
With those silver shoes,

616
00:24:50,432 --> 00:24:54,202
the Land of Oz and Emerald Castle will all be in my grasp!

617
00:24:54,462 --> 00:24:56,532
What? If that's your plan,

618
00:24:56,972 --> 00:24:59,132
I cannot give you these shoes!

619
00:24:59,202 --> 00:25:00,601
Dorothy!

620
00:25:00,602 --> 00:25:03,201
(But she ends up taking Dorothy.)

621
00:25:03,202 --> 00:25:04,642
The curtain closes.

622
00:25:06,512 --> 00:25:09,882
(They must cross the lake to save Dorothy.)

623
00:25:10,212 --> 00:25:13,152
But how should we cross the lake?

624
00:25:14,252 --> 00:25:16,121
Guys,

625
00:25:16,122 --> 00:25:18,391
let me try crossing it.

626
00:25:18,392 --> 00:25:21,122
I have strong legs,

627
00:25:21,622 --> 00:25:23,732
so I'll go and save her.

628
00:25:24,062 --> 00:25:26,632
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

629
00:25:27,302 --> 00:25:28,302
Okay.

630
00:25:28,303 --> 00:25:31,171
(He crosses the lake and punishes the Witch.)

631
00:25:31,172 --> 00:25:33,902
I can't believe you figured out my weakness.

632
00:25:34,072 --> 00:25:35,602
Water is my weakness.

633
00:25:36,572 --> 00:25:38,341
Sadly, this is it for me.

634
00:25:38,342 --> 00:25:41,542
(The Witch with intense acting leaves the stage.)

635
00:25:41,612 --> 00:25:43,481
(You're the best, Witch.)

636
00:25:43,482 --> 00:25:45,451
- The Lion has done it!
- The Lion has done it!

637
00:25:45,452 --> 00:25:47,752
- Thank you, Lion!
- Thank you, Lion!

638
00:25:48,782 --> 00:25:52,822
(Number 6, the chorus scene)

639
00:25:57,162 --> 00:25:58,731
(With courage)

640
00:25:58,732 --> 00:25:59,831
(The Lion lends a hand)

641
00:25:59,832 --> 00:26:00,832
- There you go!
- They're adorable.

642
00:26:00,833 --> 00:26:02,401
(The Scarecrow's)

643
00:26:02,402 --> 00:26:03,571
(Wisdom is so grand)

644
00:26:03,572 --> 00:26:04,631
- So cute.
- All right!

645
00:26:04,632 --> 00:26:07,402
(The best teacher is proud.)

646
00:26:08,102 --> 00:26:11,072
(Let's set out together, me and you)

647
00:26:14,612 --> 00:26:15,642
You're doing great.

648
00:26:19,382 --> 00:26:22,551
(A good friend with a heart so wide)

649
00:26:22,552 --> 00:26:23,691
(With Dorothy)

650
00:26:23,692 --> 00:26:26,292
(By our side)

651
00:26:26,352 --> 00:26:30,021
(With friends)

652
00:26:30,022 --> 00:26:31,762
(By our side)

653
00:26:33,332 --> 00:26:34,332
Yes!

654
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:35,362
(What do you think, Potato Teacher?)

655
00:26:37,272 --> 00:26:39,372
(Potato Teacher is very impressed.)

656
00:26:39,872 --> 00:26:41,442
The curtain closes.

657
00:26:41,702 --> 00:26:43,372
At the gate of the Castle.

658
00:26:43,642 --> 00:26:46,641
The curtain opens.

659
00:26:46,642 --> 00:26:47,711
(The Gatekeeper of the Emerald Castle)

660
00:26:47,712 --> 00:26:49,641
Let's go!

661
00:26:49,642 --> 00:26:51,781
(They arrive at the gate.)

662
00:26:51,782 --> 00:26:54,881
- Don't show your back.
- Sniff.

663
00:26:54,882 --> 00:26:57,151
It's nice to smell something new.

664
00:26:57,152 --> 00:27:01,422
Hi, we're here to meet the Wizard of Oz.

665
00:27:01,522 --> 00:27:05,091
You must wear these glasses before meeting him.

666
00:27:05,092 --> 00:27:07,902
Make sure to call his name after you wear them.

667
00:27:09,562 --> 00:27:12,932
(The Gatekeeper hands out black glasses.)

668
00:27:13,502 --> 00:27:14,902
Thank you.

669
00:27:14,972 --> 00:27:18,042
(They can't see anything.)

670
00:27:18,712 --> 00:27:21,942
(The Gatekeeper goes into the Castle.)

671
00:27:22,042 --> 00:27:24,552
These glasses are too dark to see anything!

672
00:27:26,612 --> 00:27:29,252
- You can't see anything. You fall.
- No!

673
00:27:29,782 --> 00:27:32,592
In 1, 2, 3.

674
00:27:32,792 --> 00:27:35,361
- Wizard of Oz!
- Wizard of Oz!

675
00:27:35,362 --> 00:27:38,131
- Open the door, please!
- Open the door, please!

676
00:27:38,132 --> 00:27:41,631
The gates open, and the Wizard is behind you.

677
00:27:41,632 --> 00:27:44,072
Keep your eyes in the front.

678
00:27:44,632 --> 00:27:45,832
Loud enough for me to hear.

679
00:27:48,572 --> 00:27:51,212
I'm the great Wizard of Oz.

680
00:27:51,712 --> 00:27:55,042
I will grant your wishes if you defeat the Wicked Witch of the West.

681
00:27:55,912 --> 00:27:57,211
The Wicked Witch of the West?

682
00:27:57,212 --> 00:28:00,081
But we had already defeated her...

683
00:28:00,082 --> 00:28:01,782
on our way here.

684
00:28:01,882 --> 00:28:03,821
That's impossible.

685
00:28:03,822 --> 00:28:05,422
How did you manage to do that?

686
00:28:05,452 --> 00:28:07,721
How did I defeat her?

687
00:28:07,722 --> 00:28:08,761
(The part where he explains how he defeated the Witch)

688
00:28:08,762 --> 00:28:10,162
Say "Start," Won Jin.

689
00:28:11,562 --> 00:28:14,331
(They practiced this in yesterday's class.)

690
00:28:14,332 --> 00:28:18,132
(Taking photos)

691
00:28:18,232 --> 00:28:20,572
Toto wears the Witch's hat.

692
00:28:20,872 --> 00:28:24,572
(As if they're taking a picture of the Wicked Witch's scene)

693
00:28:25,642 --> 00:28:28,781
(They must mime the scene.)

694
00:28:28,782 --> 00:28:30,511
Everyone, cheer!

695
00:28:30,512 --> 00:28:34,822
(The most difficult part of the play)

696
00:28:35,422 --> 00:28:36,951
Say "Start," Won Jin.

697
00:28:36,952 --> 00:28:37,952
(Can they pull this off?)

698
00:28:37,953 --> 00:28:39,152
Start.

699
00:28:39,392 --> 00:28:41,692
(North Pole Teacher will keep them on beat.)

700
00:28:41,722 --> 00:28:42,891
Witch!

701
00:28:42,892 --> 00:28:44,331
(Photo 1: Toto turns into the Witch.)

702
00:28:44,332 --> 00:28:48,201
(Photo 2: The Witch and Dorothy fight.)

703
00:28:48,202 --> 00:28:53,071
(Photo 3: Tin Man tries to be a bridge across the lake.)

704
00:28:53,072 --> 00:28:57,671
(Photo 4: Scarecrow shakes his head and tells him no.)

705
00:28:57,672 --> 00:29:02,512
(Photo 5: Lion crosses the lake and defeats the Witch.)

706
00:29:02,582 --> 00:29:06,651
(Photo 6: Everyone cheers.)

707
00:29:06,652 --> 00:29:09,082
- Yes!
- Yes!

708
00:29:09,952 --> 00:29:10,952
That was great.

709
00:29:11,852 --> 00:29:14,992
Will you grant our wishes now?

710
00:29:15,122 --> 00:29:17,992
Still, I cannot...

711
00:29:18,462 --> 00:29:21,301
Sniff, it smells the same as before.

712
00:29:21,302 --> 00:29:22,631
Sniff, sniff.

713
00:29:22,632 --> 00:29:24,401
It smells the same as before?

714
00:29:24,402 --> 00:29:25,402
That's suspicious.

715
00:29:25,832 --> 00:29:27,441
The Scarecrow approaches.

716
00:29:27,442 --> 00:29:31,812
(Something's off.)

717
00:29:32,242 --> 00:29:33,411
(He opens the curtains.)

718
00:29:33,412 --> 00:29:34,542
Oh, no!

719
00:29:37,082 --> 00:29:38,451
(They all throw away the dark glasses.)

720
00:29:38,452 --> 00:29:39,511
Okay.

721
00:29:39,512 --> 00:29:40,782
Why are you throwing them away?

722
00:29:41,482 --> 00:29:42,482
(The owner of the glasses is sad.)

723
00:29:42,483 --> 00:29:43,621
You're all throwing them.

724
00:29:43,622 --> 00:29:45,021
Wait.

725
00:29:45,022 --> 00:29:47,162
He's not the Wizard. He's the Gatekeeper from before.

726
00:29:47,192 --> 00:29:48,192
What?

727
00:29:48,193 --> 00:29:49,591
(The Wizard is fake! You lied to us?)

728
00:29:49,592 --> 00:29:51,331
- What? No.
- "Fake."

729
00:29:51,332 --> 00:29:54,002
The Wizard is fake! You lied to us?

730
00:29:54,562 --> 00:29:57,232
(They help each other out and get through the play.)

731
00:29:58,102 --> 00:30:00,741
No, I'm actually the Wizard.

732
00:30:00,742 --> 00:30:02,571
I only lied...

733
00:30:02,572 --> 00:30:05,472
because people wouldn't believe me when they saw how normal I was.

734
00:30:05,842 --> 00:30:09,042
If you really are the Wizard, grant our wishes.

735
00:30:09,642 --> 00:30:11,982
I wish to have a brain and be smart.

736
00:30:12,252 --> 00:30:14,482
I wish to be brave...

737
00:30:14,952 --> 00:30:17,152
and be the king of animals.

738
00:30:17,622 --> 00:30:21,922
I wish for a heart with a warm soul.

739
00:30:22,092 --> 00:30:24,292
I wish to go back home.

740
00:30:24,792 --> 00:30:27,662
Your wishes had already come true.

741
00:30:27,862 --> 00:30:31,971
Scarecrow figured out how to defeat the Witch,

742
00:30:31,972 --> 00:30:33,632
and he's wiser than anybody.

743
00:30:33,842 --> 00:30:37,372
Tin Man already has a warm soul and knows when to sacrifice himself.

744
00:30:38,112 --> 00:30:40,441
And Lion is...

745
00:30:40,442 --> 00:30:43,512
the brave king of all animals, who defeated the Witch.

746
00:30:43,882 --> 00:30:45,482
What about my wish?

747
00:30:45,612 --> 00:30:47,752
I wish to go back home.

748
00:30:48,252 --> 00:30:49,421
That's really simple.

749
00:30:49,422 --> 00:30:52,021
See the silver shoes on your feet?

750
00:30:52,022 --> 00:30:54,592
Tap them three times and say your wish.

751
00:30:54,892 --> 00:30:55,922
Really?

752
00:30:55,962 --> 00:30:58,362
I can finally go back home!

753
00:30:59,562 --> 00:31:02,502
(They all got their wishes.)

754
00:31:05,032 --> 00:31:08,942
All right, then. To my home and my beloved family,

755
00:31:09,242 --> 00:31:10,372
we go!

756
00:31:11,142 --> 00:31:13,881
(Stomping her silver shoes)

757
00:31:13,882 --> 00:31:15,881
Everyone cheers!

758
00:31:15,882 --> 00:31:19,882
(Their adventure in the Land of Oz ends.)

759
00:31:19,912 --> 00:31:21,251
Wizard!

760
00:31:21,252 --> 00:31:23,622
(Cheering quietly)

761
00:31:24,192 --> 00:31:26,421
(The narrator will finish the play.)

762
00:31:26,422 --> 00:31:28,791
Everyone finally got...

763
00:31:28,792 --> 00:31:30,592
their long-awaited wishes.

764
00:31:31,162 --> 00:31:34,932
If you have a wish, try looking within.

765
00:31:35,862 --> 00:31:38,732
You might already have that quality.

766
00:31:39,032 --> 00:31:42,101
(Good job memorizing your lines, narrator.)

767
00:31:42,102 --> 00:31:44,711
The play ends.

768
00:31:44,712 --> 00:31:46,511
- Bow, everyone.
- Bow!

769
00:31:46,512 --> 00:31:47,512
(The run-through ends.)

770
00:31:48,182 --> 00:31:49,311
Give it up!

771
00:31:49,312 --> 00:31:50,411
Give it up!

772
00:31:50,412 --> 00:31:51,512
(Clap for yourselves.)

773
00:31:51,882 --> 00:31:54,382
I saw a possibility.

774
00:31:54,922 --> 00:31:56,221
They got some of the lines wrong,

775
00:31:56,222 --> 00:31:59,621
but they remembered most of the movements and lines.

776
00:31:59,622 --> 00:32:03,462
We got this far only with nine classes.

777
00:32:03,862 --> 00:32:08,062
It occurred to me how impressive they were.

778
00:32:09,362 --> 00:32:11,502
They're all doing great,

779
00:32:11,772 --> 00:32:14,142
but they seem to lack confidence.

780
00:32:14,302 --> 00:32:17,211
I'm worried they'll stay that way until the actual performance.

781
00:32:17,212 --> 00:32:18,672
(Their lack of confidence still needs fixing.)

782
00:32:19,212 --> 00:32:21,111
I'd like to...

783
00:32:21,112 --> 00:32:24,781
take the time to talk to them in private...

784
00:32:24,782 --> 00:32:26,211
after class.

785
00:32:26,212 --> 00:32:27,252
(A private date with the kids)

786
00:32:28,752 --> 00:32:30,792
Ha Yun, I'm starving.

787
00:32:30,852 --> 00:32:31,852
- Aren't you hungry?
- Right.

788
00:32:31,853 --> 00:32:33,422
- I'm hungry.
- I'm starving.

789
00:32:34,062 --> 00:32:35,691
You usually get hungry around this time, don't you?

790
00:32:35,692 --> 00:32:37,462
(Potato Teacher and Ha Yun are still at school after class.)

791
00:32:37,592 --> 00:32:38,732
Let's eat.

792
00:32:38,792 --> 00:32:39,931
Thank you for the food.

793
00:32:39,932 --> 00:32:42,102
(They have dinner first.)

794
00:32:42,762 --> 00:32:44,672
(Exclaiming)

795
00:32:44,972 --> 00:32:47,601
- This is so good. Right?
- Yes.

796
00:32:47,602 --> 00:32:48,602
(He shows it with his eyebrows yet again.)

797
00:32:49,842 --> 00:32:52,542
(A big bite)

798
00:32:52,772 --> 00:32:54,442
You're going to eat the paper too.

799
00:32:55,812 --> 00:32:57,212
- You must have been hungry.
- Yes.

800
00:32:58,812 --> 00:33:00,351
(Devouring it)

801
00:33:00,352 --> 00:33:01,922
You eat really fast.

802
00:33:03,952 --> 00:33:05,652
- When I was in elementary school...
- Yes.

803
00:33:06,522 --> 00:33:08,692
You know the small Yukgaejang cup ramyeon?

804
00:33:09,422 --> 00:33:10,792
I had 12 of those.

805
00:33:11,992 --> 00:33:13,032
Cool, right?

806
00:33:13,592 --> 00:33:14,632
Yes.

807
00:33:15,602 --> 00:33:16,861
- I'm not lying.
- Okay.

808
00:33:16,862 --> 00:33:18,131
I was that hungry.

809
00:33:18,132 --> 00:33:20,471
(This 25-year-old shows off how much he can eat...)

810
00:33:20,472 --> 00:33:22,242
(with sauce all over his mouth.)

811
00:33:23,442 --> 00:33:24,772
- Is the play fun?
- Yes.

812
00:33:25,042 --> 00:33:26,171
What's the most fun?

813
00:33:26,172 --> 00:33:28,082
(Thinking)

814
00:33:28,642 --> 00:33:30,712
All of it.

815
00:33:32,012 --> 00:33:33,312
What's the toughest part?

816
00:33:34,622 --> 00:33:36,181
- The lines?
- No.

817
00:33:36,182 --> 00:33:37,391
Then, what? Tell me just one.

818
00:33:37,392 --> 00:33:39,691
- Standing in front of people...
- And performing?

819
00:33:39,692 --> 00:33:40,722
Yes.

820
00:33:41,592 --> 00:33:42,762
Why is that hard?

821
00:33:43,162 --> 00:33:44,962
- It just makes me nervous.
- What?

822
00:33:45,132 --> 00:33:46,161
- It makes me nervous.
- Nervous?

823
00:33:46,162 --> 00:33:47,532
When there are too many people.

824
00:33:47,962 --> 00:33:50,162
What do you think you should do to stop being nervous?

825
00:33:50,502 --> 00:33:52,132
- Right?
- I don't know.

826
00:33:53,132 --> 00:33:54,942
I'm always nervous.

827
00:33:55,172 --> 00:33:56,802
- What?
- But...

828
00:33:57,512 --> 00:33:59,241
once I cast a spell on myself,

829
00:33:59,242 --> 00:34:01,442
"This moment never comes back,"

830
00:34:01,812 --> 00:34:03,811
- and I'm no longer nervous.
- Okay.

831
00:34:03,812 --> 00:34:05,812
We're doing it anyway,

832
00:34:06,052 --> 00:34:07,422
- so let's cheer up.
- Okay.

833
00:34:07,552 --> 00:34:10,181
I'll try not to be embarrassed,

834
00:34:10,182 --> 00:34:11,791
- so let's both try.
- Okay.

835
00:34:11,792 --> 00:34:12,992
- All right?
- Okay.

836
00:34:14,022 --> 00:34:15,221
- You promised.
- Yes.

837
00:34:15,222 --> 00:34:16,562
- Do you want to play baseball?
- Yes.

838
00:34:16,992 --> 00:34:18,762
- Do you want to know the pitches?
- Yes.

839
00:34:19,562 --> 00:34:21,061
- The different grips, I mean.
- Yes.

840
00:34:21,062 --> 00:34:23,232
(He tries to help him relax with baseball.)

841
00:34:24,202 --> 00:34:25,802
What kind of pitch grip do you want to know?

842
00:34:26,572 --> 00:34:27,601
The splitter.

843
00:34:27,602 --> 00:34:28,742
- Splitter?
- Yes.

844
00:34:29,072 --> 00:34:30,871
There are two types of grips for throwing a splitter.

845
00:34:30,872 --> 00:34:31,872
Okay.

846
00:34:31,972 --> 00:34:34,382
Go like this and flick your wrist.

847
00:34:36,582 --> 00:34:37,651
- How was that?
- Yes.

848
00:34:37,652 --> 00:34:38,782
- Good, right?
- Yes.

849
00:34:39,552 --> 00:34:41,081
- It felt the same as a fastball.
- What?

850
00:34:41,082 --> 00:34:42,481
- Nothing.
- You don't like it?

851
00:34:42,482 --> 00:34:43,991
It felt the same as a fastball.

852
00:34:43,992 --> 00:34:45,221
- It felt the same as a fastball?
- Yes.

853
00:34:45,222 --> 00:34:47,692
- That's because you're bad at it.
- What?

854
00:34:47,922 --> 00:34:49,422
- This is a fastball grip.
- Yes.

855
00:34:49,592 --> 00:34:51,362
That ball goes straight.

856
00:34:52,192 --> 00:34:53,562
- That's a fastball.
- Yes.

857
00:34:54,362 --> 00:34:55,431
But a splitter is different.

858
00:34:55,432 --> 00:34:57,532
- You have to use a wrist snap.
- Okay.

859
00:34:57,632 --> 00:34:58,802
Like this.

860
00:34:59,302 --> 00:35:01,342
Which stitches do I touch?

861
00:35:01,672 --> 00:35:02,701
- The stitches?
- Yes.

862
00:35:02,702 --> 00:35:04,512
- Like this.
- Okay.

863
00:35:05,012 --> 00:35:06,742
How about the knuckle curve?

864
00:35:07,112 --> 00:35:10,242
The knuckle curve? Well, I couldn't go pro, so...

865
00:35:10,682 --> 00:35:12,081
- Like this?
- Yes.

866
00:35:12,082 --> 00:35:13,112
Try it.

867
00:35:14,452 --> 00:35:17,252
(It's certainly stronger now.)

868
00:35:17,992 --> 00:35:19,421
How about we give a shout with a loud voice?

869
00:35:19,422 --> 00:35:20,452
No.

870
00:35:20,552 --> 00:35:21,662
- What?
- Yes?

871
00:35:21,792 --> 00:35:23,361
- We have a play to perform.
- Yes.

872
00:35:23,362 --> 00:35:24,491
- Right?
- Yes.

873
00:35:24,492 --> 00:35:27,032
- At this moment, we're actors.
- Okay.

874
00:35:27,132 --> 00:35:28,731
Our job is to deliver it to that person over there.

875
00:35:28,732 --> 00:35:30,402
Just like we deliver a baseball.

876
00:35:30,602 --> 00:35:31,701
- Yes.
- But...

877
00:35:31,702 --> 00:35:34,072
in a play, you use your voice instead of a baseball.

878
00:35:34,402 --> 00:35:36,942
Imagine breaking that window...

879
00:35:37,272 --> 00:35:38,672
with your voice.

880
00:35:40,072 --> 00:35:41,282
Use your imagination.

881
00:35:42,142 --> 00:35:43,312
Start.

882
00:35:48,352 --> 00:35:49,352
- Yes.
- All right.

883
00:35:49,353 --> 00:35:50,722
- Let's just throw the ball.
- Okay.

884
00:35:52,092 --> 00:35:53,852
- Can you throw farther?
- What?

885
00:35:53,952 --> 00:35:55,622
- Farther.
- What?

886
00:35:56,122 --> 00:35:57,462
- Can you do it?
- Yes.

887
00:35:58,632 --> 00:35:59,992
I can't hear you.

888
00:36:00,662 --> 00:36:01,961
- Yes!
- Good.

889
00:36:01,962 --> 00:36:02,962
(Yes!)

890
00:36:02,963 --> 00:36:05,072
Let's play catch while shouting, "We are one."

891
00:36:05,432 --> 00:36:06,532
Sound off.

892
00:36:07,032 --> 00:36:08,841
I'll go first. We are...

893
00:36:08,842 --> 00:36:10,541
(We are...)

894
00:36:10,542 --> 00:36:12,142
- One!
- Good.

895
00:36:13,842 --> 00:36:15,082
From tomorrow!

896
00:36:16,642 --> 00:36:17,782
We are...

897
00:36:19,112 --> 00:36:20,211
One!

898
00:36:20,212 --> 00:36:21,722
(Screaming)

899
00:36:22,452 --> 00:36:24,022
We can do it!

900
00:36:24,492 --> 00:36:26,392
Louder. We can do it!

901
00:36:28,522 --> 00:36:29,622
Louder!

902
00:36:29,992 --> 00:36:31,491
We can do it!

903
00:36:31,492 --> 00:36:32,562
All right!

904
00:36:33,662 --> 00:36:35,602
We have to come up with a chant for tomorrow. What's yours?

905
00:36:36,102 --> 00:36:37,361
- Nothing.
- Nothing?

906
00:36:37,362 --> 00:36:39,172
- Yes.
- Shout, "Nothing."

907
00:36:40,172 --> 00:36:41,342
Nothing!

908
00:36:44,742 --> 00:36:45,771
That's good.

909
00:36:45,772 --> 00:36:47,741
Do you see how the ball landed in this zone...

910
00:36:47,742 --> 00:36:49,481
- because you shouted?
- Yes.

911
00:36:49,482 --> 00:36:50,682
- Right?
- Yes.

912
00:36:51,652 --> 00:36:54,352
The catcher is your audience in baseball.

913
00:36:54,752 --> 00:36:55,851
Got it?

914
00:36:55,852 --> 00:36:58,122
- Deliver it to the audience.
- Okay.

915
00:36:58,852 --> 00:37:00,052
- You promise?
- Yes.

916
00:37:00,962 --> 00:37:01,992
Let's go!

917
00:37:02,992 --> 00:37:04,892
- Let's go!
- There you go.

918
00:37:06,532 --> 00:37:07,902
- Is your house close?
- Yes.

919
00:37:08,002 --> 00:37:10,731
- How close?
- It's about 200m.

920
00:37:10,732 --> 00:37:13,131
It's 200m away? You could have gone by yourself.

921
00:37:13,132 --> 00:37:14,701
(These two seem like close friends.)

922
00:37:14,702 --> 00:37:17,042
- It's 100m and 200m.
- It's 100m?

923
00:37:17,612 --> 00:37:19,271
(Whose is this?)

924
00:37:19,272 --> 00:37:20,542
(Is it okay if I use this?)

925
00:37:21,042 --> 00:37:23,242
(Just use it.)

926
00:37:23,782 --> 00:37:26,511
(They joke around every time they get a chance.)

927
00:37:26,512 --> 00:37:28,881
- There's no rice.
- Scrape the bowl...

928
00:37:28,882 --> 00:37:29,882
(Sometimes, the power dynamic shifts.)

929
00:37:29,883 --> 00:37:31,892
(Scraping)

930
00:37:33,252 --> 00:37:37,022
(A teacher and a student who are 30 years apart)

931
00:37:37,862 --> 00:37:40,162
(But they have fun when they're together.)

932
00:37:41,702 --> 00:37:44,302
(Are you hurt?)

933
00:37:45,932 --> 00:37:47,842
(Blowing on it)

934
00:37:49,342 --> 00:37:53,072
(They're closer than anybody else.)

935
00:37:54,642 --> 00:37:58,752
(Tom and Jerry of acting class, North Pole Teacher and Won Jin)

936
00:37:58,982 --> 00:38:00,212
Turn on the flashlight.

937
00:38:01,082 --> 00:38:02,682
- Why would I turn it on?
- What?

938
00:38:03,152 --> 00:38:05,622
- Why would I?
- We'll go in the dark, then.

939
00:38:06,192 --> 00:38:07,662
- We're men, after all.
- Exactly.

940
00:38:09,322 --> 00:38:11,662
- I guess no one lives here.
- It's a deserted house.

941
00:38:11,832 --> 00:38:13,461
- The one on the right too?
- Yes.

942
00:38:13,462 --> 00:38:14,831
- This is a deserted house?
- Yes.

943
00:38:14,832 --> 00:38:16,632
(Exclaiming)

944
00:38:17,432 --> 00:38:18,601
(Surprised)

945
00:38:18,602 --> 00:38:20,532
- Who is that man?
- What?

946
00:38:22,472 --> 00:38:24,612
It's scary going around at night, isn't it?

947
00:38:24,872 --> 00:38:26,311
I'm not scared. You're scared, aren't you?

948
00:38:26,312 --> 00:38:28,012
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

949
00:38:29,142 --> 00:38:30,182
You're scared.

950
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:32,112
See? You're holding my hand tightly.

951
00:38:32,952 --> 00:38:34,652
(Jeez)

952
00:38:35,382 --> 00:38:36,651
I'm going back to school.

953
00:38:36,652 --> 00:38:39,092
Fine. Let's go home.

954
00:38:39,392 --> 00:38:41,291
Come on. Let's go home.

955
00:38:41,292 --> 00:38:42,321
Bye.

956
00:38:42,322 --> 00:38:43,622
I'll wait at your house, then.

957
00:38:44,292 --> 00:38:46,091
- Fine.
- I'll wait there.

958
00:38:46,092 --> 00:38:48,162
- Fine. Run there.
- I'll wait there.

959
00:38:48,462 --> 00:38:49,802
I'll wait at your house.

960
00:38:50,302 --> 00:38:51,431
Is the grocery store open?

961
00:38:51,432 --> 00:38:53,271
- The grocery store?
- Yes.

962
00:38:53,272 --> 00:38:54,402
It is open.

963
00:38:55,242 --> 00:38:56,842
He and I are close.

964
00:38:57,102 --> 00:38:58,141
I see.

965
00:38:58,142 --> 00:39:00,342
- He's an elder.
- Mother-in-law?

966
00:39:00,572 --> 00:39:02,782
- Elder!
- Oh, an elder.

967
00:39:03,142 --> 00:39:04,382
I thought you were married.

968
00:39:04,982 --> 00:39:06,482
- Come on.
- What?

969
00:39:07,112 --> 00:39:08,621
Hi, there.

970
00:39:08,622 --> 00:39:10,722
- Hello. Do you know her?
- Yes.

971
00:39:10,852 --> 00:39:12,251
- Who is she?
- Hi.

972
00:39:12,252 --> 00:39:13,552
(Hi, camera.)

973
00:39:14,022 --> 00:39:15,992
- This is your house, right?
- No.

974
00:39:16,322 --> 00:39:17,491
- What is it?
- Over there.

975
00:39:17,492 --> 00:39:19,191
Go inside. I'll be here.

976
00:39:19,192 --> 00:39:20,531
- Go inside.
- Okay.

977
00:39:20,532 --> 00:39:21,562
Won Jin.

978
00:39:22,702 --> 00:39:25,302
(Looking intently)

979
00:39:27,602 --> 00:39:30,542
(Rushing)

980
00:39:33,412 --> 00:39:35,441
(Tom and Jerry don't want to say goodbye just yet.)

981
00:39:35,442 --> 00:39:37,112
Bye.

982
00:39:41,052 --> 00:39:42,052
Bye.

983
00:39:42,382 --> 00:39:43,752
See you tomorrow. Don't be late.

984
00:39:47,192 --> 00:39:49,422
(Sighing)

985
00:39:51,932 --> 00:39:53,231
(Staring)

986
00:39:53,232 --> 00:39:55,102
What did they set up here?

987
00:39:58,932 --> 00:40:01,642
(Stealthily)

988
00:40:04,572 --> 00:40:05,642
Go home.

989
00:40:06,772 --> 00:40:10,011
(He can't seem to leave.)

990
00:40:10,012 --> 00:40:11,282
Go home, sir.

991
00:40:14,622 --> 00:40:17,182
(North Pole Teacher can't get his eyes off him.)

992
00:40:18,922 --> 00:40:19,951
Dad!

993
00:40:19,952 --> 00:40:21,921
(Won Jin returns home.)

994
00:40:21,922 --> 00:40:23,021
- Hyo Min.
- Yes?

995
00:40:23,022 --> 00:40:25,361
- What do you want to eat?
- This looks the most delicious.

996
00:40:25,362 --> 00:40:26,932
- Should we eat that?
- Yes.

997
00:40:27,902 --> 00:40:29,761
On our camping yesterday, you said your dream was...

998
00:40:29,762 --> 00:40:31,502
- to be an actor, right?
- Yes.

999
00:40:31,602 --> 00:40:33,332
It was fun when I tried it out.

1000
00:40:33,672 --> 00:40:34,802
During this acting class?

1001
00:40:35,272 --> 00:40:38,012
You started dreaming of becoming an actor in my class?

1002
00:40:38,112 --> 00:40:39,112
Yes.

1003
00:40:39,372 --> 00:40:40,372
That's lovely.

1004
00:40:40,373 --> 00:40:42,442
And we haven't even put on the play yet.

1005
00:40:43,312 --> 00:40:46,182
But you'll be gone once we do the play.

1006
00:40:47,782 --> 00:40:50,422
If you keep dreaming of becoming an actor,

1007
00:40:51,292 --> 00:40:52,752
we might see each other often.

1008
00:40:53,022 --> 00:40:54,562
Because I'll continue to be an actor.

1009
00:40:55,422 --> 00:40:56,792
I don't think we'll meet again.

1010
00:40:57,692 --> 00:40:59,432
- Later...
- I don't think you'll recognize me.

1011
00:40:59,932 --> 00:41:01,002
You?

1012
00:41:01,332 --> 00:41:04,931
Your face changes as you grow older, you know.

1013
00:41:04,932 --> 00:41:06,972
I looked exactly the same as I was when I was little.

1014
00:41:07,302 --> 00:41:09,242
- Show me.
- I think you'll grow up the same.

1015
00:41:09,302 --> 00:41:11,442
- Show me, then.
- Show you my childhood photos?

1016
00:41:11,542 --> 00:41:12,542
Yes.

1017
00:41:15,342 --> 00:41:16,811
(Presenting evidence)

1018
00:41:16,812 --> 00:41:18,052
That's you?

1019
00:41:18,912 --> 00:41:22,022
"Kim Tae Ri's elementary school graduation photo."

1020
00:41:22,982 --> 00:41:24,792
- You look similar.
- Right?

1021
00:41:24,852 --> 00:41:26,991
- But...
- You're going to look the same.

1022
00:41:26,992 --> 00:41:28,561
- But...
- You'll look exactly the same.

1023
00:41:28,562 --> 00:41:29,562
Our food is here.

1024
00:41:29,563 --> 00:41:31,991
- Here's your food.
- Thank you so much.

1025
00:41:31,992 --> 00:41:33,631
- Perfect timing.
- Thank you.

1026
00:41:33,632 --> 00:41:35,532
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1027
00:41:35,632 --> 00:41:37,461
- I'll eat a chicken leg.
- Okay.

1028
00:41:37,462 --> 00:41:39,801
I'll eat the cheese balls while you do.

1029
00:41:39,802 --> 00:41:40,802
Okay.

1030
00:41:40,803 --> 00:41:43,342
(Crispy)

1031
00:41:43,772 --> 00:41:45,011
(Stretching)

1032
00:41:45,012 --> 00:41:46,311
Hyo Min, you know...

1033
00:41:46,312 --> 00:41:48,811
you can ask me anything about the play...

1034
00:41:48,812 --> 00:41:52,011
as you practice, and I'll answer you, right?

1035
00:41:52,012 --> 00:41:54,252
- Yes. But...
- Yes?

1036
00:41:54,482 --> 00:41:57,352
some of the lines are too difficult.

1037
00:41:57,552 --> 00:41:59,152
The lines are difficult?

1038
00:41:59,352 --> 00:42:01,291
What if I make a mistake during the play?

1039
00:42:01,292 --> 00:42:03,061
Like a huge mistake.

1040
00:42:03,062 --> 00:42:04,161
That doesn't matter.

1041
00:42:04,162 --> 00:42:06,562
One big mistake to ruin the whole play.

1042
00:42:06,762 --> 00:42:08,931
Even if you make that mistake,

1043
00:42:08,932 --> 00:42:11,102
your friends will be there to help you.

1044
00:42:11,202 --> 00:42:14,301
But I feel like people will laugh at me.

1045
00:42:14,302 --> 00:42:18,071
No, not at all. No one will laugh at you.

1046
00:42:18,072 --> 00:42:20,011
Take my word for it.

1047
00:42:20,012 --> 00:42:23,212
What if I just can't get the lines right during practice?

1048
00:42:25,212 --> 00:42:27,781
No matter how you do on the stage,

1049
00:42:27,782 --> 00:42:30,482
I'll clap for you and be happy for you.

1050
00:42:30,652 --> 00:42:32,322
You said you'd give your best,

1051
00:42:32,622 --> 00:42:34,052
and I believe you.

1052
00:42:34,792 --> 00:42:35,961
- Right?
- Yes.

1053
00:42:35,962 --> 00:42:37,091
(Ms. Kim wants to give him courage through faith.)

1054
00:42:37,092 --> 00:42:40,232
I completely understand what you're thinking.

1055
00:42:40,462 --> 00:42:42,632
But what do you need to do in return?

1056
00:42:43,032 --> 00:42:44,971
Participate more actively.

1057
00:42:44,972 --> 00:42:46,572
So, you know!

1058
00:42:48,042 --> 00:42:49,602
You know it.

1059
00:42:49,772 --> 00:42:52,312
I'll try to be as energetic as I can be.

1060
00:42:52,442 --> 00:42:54,242
- You'll do your best?
- Yes.

1061
00:42:54,612 --> 00:42:57,081
It's okay to make mistakes and break...

1062
00:42:57,082 --> 00:42:58,481
(Their rehearsal is happening soon.)

1063
00:42:58,482 --> 00:43:01,522
I asked myself what might be the most important thing.

1064
00:43:01,622 --> 00:43:03,422
"Let's do this together, guys!"

1065
00:43:04,322 --> 00:43:06,951
I think it's important for us to be enthusiastic together.

1066
00:43:06,952 --> 00:43:07,962
Also, confidence.

1067
00:43:09,422 --> 00:43:12,192
It would be great if they could pour all that out.

1068
00:43:13,032 --> 00:43:14,502
I hope they'll be able to do it.

1069
00:43:15,202 --> 00:43:16,202
I know they can.

1070
00:43:18,232 --> 00:43:20,471
Guess what I brought from home.

1071
00:43:20,472 --> 00:43:21,472
What?

1072
00:43:21,742 --> 00:43:23,672
Take it from under the table.

1073
00:43:23,772 --> 00:43:24,812
What?

1074
00:43:25,212 --> 00:43:27,472
Why? What is this? Is this Pepero?

1075
00:43:28,842 --> 00:43:30,711
I see! It's Ms. Kim's love.

1076
00:43:30,712 --> 00:43:32,181
(Also giving him some of her love)

1077
00:43:32,182 --> 00:43:33,811
You know how much love I have for you guys, don't you?

1078
00:43:33,812 --> 00:43:35,081
Of course.

1079
00:43:35,082 --> 00:43:37,682
By the way, I will never eat this.

1080
00:43:38,822 --> 00:43:39,851
(Moved)

1081
00:43:39,852 --> 00:43:41,692
This is something I can't eat.

1082
00:43:41,792 --> 00:43:43,491
I won't ever eat it.

1083
00:43:43,492 --> 00:43:44,492
(He wants to cherish it forever.)

1084
00:43:44,493 --> 00:43:45,732
You should eat it.

1085
00:43:46,162 --> 00:43:49,961
Should we end the day after saying our last words?

1086
00:43:49,962 --> 00:43:51,232
All right. Say your last words.

1087
00:43:51,332 --> 00:43:52,402
What is it?

1088
00:43:52,502 --> 00:43:56,601
Ms. Kim, I will show you from below the table.

1089
00:43:56,602 --> 00:43:57,702
Okay.

1090
00:43:58,042 --> 00:44:00,311
Ms. Kim, you have to keep this a secret from the others.

1091
00:44:00,312 --> 00:44:01,312
Okay.

1092
00:44:01,512 --> 00:44:03,141
Take a look.

1093
00:44:03,142 --> 00:44:04,142
No, from below!

1094
00:44:04,143 --> 00:44:06,911
Okay, okay!

1095
00:44:06,912 --> 00:44:09,152
One, two, three. The end.

1096
00:44:09,852 --> 00:44:11,491
- Please do it one more time.
- No.

1097
00:44:11,492 --> 00:44:13,191
Come on, please.

1098
00:44:13,192 --> 00:44:16,692
- Show me one more time.
- Okay. The end.

1099
00:44:18,432 --> 00:44:19,531
Did you take a picture of it?

1100
00:44:19,532 --> 00:44:20,561
No, I didn't.

1101
00:44:20,562 --> 00:44:21,801
You took a picture. I heard a sound.

1102
00:44:21,802 --> 00:44:23,262
- No.
- I think you did.

1103
00:44:23,662 --> 00:44:25,031
- I didn't take a picture.
- Look. Cheesecake...

1104
00:44:25,032 --> 00:44:26,672
I took a picture of it with my eyes.

1105
00:44:30,702 --> 00:44:33,241
Let's meet tomorrow.

1106
00:44:33,242 --> 00:44:34,442
Okay, see you tomorrow.

1107
00:44:38,352 --> 00:44:41,922
(Crunching)

1108
00:44:43,952 --> 00:44:45,292
How far did Tae Ri go?

1109
00:44:46,792 --> 00:44:48,622
(Staring blankly)

1110
00:44:49,322 --> 00:44:50,391
Aren't you hungry?

1111
00:44:50,392 --> 00:44:52,662
(Nodding)

1112
00:44:55,732 --> 00:44:57,301
(Crunch)

1113
00:44:57,302 --> 00:44:58,331
Why is this so good?

1114
00:44:58,332 --> 00:44:59,832
How is it so good?

1115
00:45:01,742 --> 00:45:02,841
What is up with that?

1116
00:45:02,842 --> 00:45:05,642
(The apple addicts are curious.)

1117
00:45:05,742 --> 00:45:07,372
There must be a separate stomach for delicious things.

1118
00:45:07,982 --> 00:45:08,982
Sure.

1119
00:45:10,882 --> 00:45:11,912
She's back.

1120
00:45:13,352 --> 00:45:14,412
I hear fried chicken.

1121
00:45:14,622 --> 00:45:15,922
It sounds like fried chicken, right?

1122
00:45:16,452 --> 00:45:18,422
She brought back fried chicken.

1123
00:45:20,192 --> 00:45:21,322
I told you.

1124
00:45:22,622 --> 00:45:25,292
(It's fried chicken!)

1125
00:45:27,232 --> 00:45:28,232
Here.

1126
00:45:28,402 --> 00:45:30,602
- Thank you for the food.
- This is amazing.

1127
00:45:30,962 --> 00:45:32,631
Do you want gloves? Plastic gloves?

1128
00:45:32,632 --> 00:45:34,472
Was that why you went there? You're so fast.

1129
00:45:34,572 --> 00:45:35,901
When did you go?

1130
00:45:35,902 --> 00:45:36,942
(He's fast to greet the chicken.)

1131
00:45:37,042 --> 00:45:38,272
You were just here.

1132
00:45:38,742 --> 00:45:40,712
(Crunch)

1133
00:45:41,072 --> 00:45:42,541
I haven't had fried chicken in a while.

1134
00:45:42,542 --> 00:45:43,542
(I haven't had fried chicken in a while.)

1135
00:45:44,212 --> 00:45:45,212
What is this?

1136
00:45:45,213 --> 00:45:47,152
(This is not a sponsored product.)

1137
00:45:47,512 --> 00:45:48,552
Is it Bburinkle?

1138
00:45:49,152 --> 00:45:50,222
Is it Bburinkle?

1139
00:45:51,622 --> 00:45:53,291
Just fried chicken and spicy fried chicken.

1140
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:54,292
(I'm fried chicken...)

1141
00:45:54,293 --> 00:45:55,662
No Bburinkle?

1142
00:45:57,792 --> 00:45:59,531
I've already eaten, so go ahead!

1143
00:45:59,532 --> 00:46:00,931
- Did you eat?
- Yes.

1144
00:46:00,932 --> 00:46:03,032
- Tae Ri, did you buy Bburinkle?
- Yes?

1145
00:46:04,162 --> 00:46:05,602
Don't say such a thing. Just eat it.

1146
00:46:08,402 --> 00:46:10,302
(What did you say?)

1147
00:46:10,602 --> 00:46:11,672
I love it.

1148
00:46:11,772 --> 00:46:13,371
- Are you happy?
- Yes. Totally.

1149
00:46:13,372 --> 00:46:15,542
- Okay.
- This is amazing.

1150
00:46:18,312 --> 00:46:21,152
(Hyun Wook is slightly disappointed.)

1151
00:46:23,152 --> 00:46:26,052
(Singing)

1152
00:46:26,492 --> 00:46:28,691
(Laughing)

1153
00:46:28,692 --> 00:46:30,692
I've been singing this song all day. How crazy.

1154
00:46:32,092 --> 00:46:34,092
(Happy late-night snack time)

1155
00:46:35,062 --> 00:46:36,862
(Biting)

1156
00:46:37,832 --> 00:46:39,772
(It tastes great.)

1157
00:46:39,972 --> 00:46:41,002
Great.

1158
00:46:46,412 --> 00:46:49,382
(Hyun Wook is taking a big bite too.)

1159
00:46:50,082 --> 00:46:52,082
(Sighing)

1160
00:46:54,412 --> 00:46:55,822
I haven't had this in a while.

1161
00:46:59,852 --> 00:47:02,091
(Food-eating show with late-night snackers)

1162
00:47:02,092 --> 00:47:03,592
- It's good.
- Yes.

1163
00:47:05,162 --> 00:47:07,662
I've never had regular fried chicken from this brand before.

1164
00:47:09,532 --> 00:47:11,532
(Something feels missing.)

1165
00:47:11,832 --> 00:47:13,132
There are no cheese balls.

1166
00:47:16,672 --> 00:47:17,672
Am I being greedy?

1167
00:47:20,112 --> 00:47:22,212
- Is it good?
- It's delicious!

1168
00:47:24,512 --> 00:47:25,512
What?

1169
00:47:25,513 --> 00:47:27,212
(Moved by how fast Kangnam can change attitudes)

1170
00:47:27,852 --> 00:47:29,822
- It's very delicious.
- Is it?

1171
00:47:31,792 --> 00:47:35,092
(Is this what the adults call social life?)

1172
00:47:36,392 --> 00:47:37,621
(After devouring the fried chicken)

1173
00:47:37,622 --> 00:47:38,831
- I'm sleepy.
- I'm done eating.

1174
00:47:38,832 --> 00:47:41,032
By the way, where is the Bburinkle flavor?

1175
00:47:42,232 --> 00:47:43,432
(Studying)

1176
00:47:43,702 --> 00:47:45,372
I'm okay without it, but he needs...

1177
00:47:46,572 --> 00:47:48,572
He keeps on mentioning it.

1178
00:47:48,872 --> 00:47:50,541
I told him to let it go. This is enough.

1179
00:47:50,542 --> 00:47:52,841
But when I asked you what you wanted to eat,

1180
00:47:52,842 --> 00:47:54,572
you told me fried chicken and spicy fried chicken.

1181
00:47:54,842 --> 00:47:55,941
Then it's your fault.

1182
00:47:55,942 --> 00:47:57,841
- That was what you said.
- That's true.

1183
00:47:57,842 --> 00:47:59,352
What did you eat there?

1184
00:47:59,452 --> 00:48:01,282
- Bburinkle.
- Really?

1185
00:48:01,582 --> 00:48:04,422
- Are you serious? Really?
- What? Really?

1186
00:48:05,222 --> 00:48:06,891
But I asked what you wanted...

1187
00:48:06,892 --> 00:48:08,261
- Hold on.
- Come on.

1188
00:48:08,262 --> 00:48:09,721
- You said spicy fried chicken.
- What is this?

1189
00:48:09,722 --> 00:48:10,722
Hold on.

1190
00:48:10,723 --> 00:48:12,261
- You ate Bburinkle?
- That was what you said.

1191
00:48:12,262 --> 00:48:14,691
You had Bburinkle,

1192
00:48:14,692 --> 00:48:16,031
but you bought us this?

1193
00:48:16,032 --> 00:48:17,431
- I mean, I like this too.
- Me too.

1194
00:48:17,432 --> 00:48:19,432
If you had something similar,

1195
00:48:20,002 --> 00:48:22,441
I would understand.

1196
00:48:22,442 --> 00:48:24,942
But you had Bburinkle.

1197
00:48:25,372 --> 00:48:27,071
The thing is, I only mentioned Bburinkle.

1198
00:48:27,072 --> 00:48:28,912
He mentioned cheese balls.

1199
00:48:29,342 --> 00:48:30,742
I had cheese balls too.

1200
00:48:32,312 --> 00:48:34,852
(Scolding with his eyes)

1201
00:48:35,882 --> 00:48:37,922
He was craving cheese balls.

1202
00:48:38,022 --> 00:48:39,451
If she had some,

1203
00:48:39,452 --> 00:48:41,352
- she should've ordered one for us.
- I agree.

1204
00:48:41,462 --> 00:48:42,821
She ate everything we wanted.

1205
00:48:42,822 --> 00:48:43,862
Exactly.

1206
00:48:44,292 --> 00:48:45,531
This is wrong.

1207
00:48:45,532 --> 00:48:46,591
(Anyway, thank you for the food.)

1208
00:48:46,592 --> 00:48:47,662
I see.

1209
00:48:48,702 --> 00:48:50,432
- Now...
- Rehearsal.

1210
00:48:50,802 --> 00:48:52,002
Tomorrow is the stage rehearsal.

1211
00:48:52,102 --> 00:48:54,802
We'll try everything with the costumes on.

1212
00:48:55,242 --> 00:48:57,501
Shouldn't we have...

1213
00:48:57,502 --> 00:48:59,942
- a curtain call?
- Dorothy!

1214
00:49:00,412 --> 00:49:03,381
CO KUN is working hard on the music for it.

1215
00:49:03,382 --> 00:49:04,441
Right.

1216
00:49:04,442 --> 00:49:06,612
While the music is playing, you should appear too.

1217
00:49:07,252 --> 00:49:09,382
I should keep moderating. "Next up..."

1218
00:49:09,482 --> 00:49:11,991
Yes, you'll be the one to do it. "Everyone, bow!"

1219
00:49:11,992 --> 00:49:13,522
Then they can bow together.

1220
00:49:13,722 --> 00:49:14,722
I bet they know...

1221
00:49:14,723 --> 00:49:16,022
- curtain calls.
- I should call the teachers.

1222
00:49:16,922 --> 00:49:18,491
How should I introduce him?

1223
00:49:18,492 --> 00:49:19,632
- Potato Teacher.
- Lackey.

1224
00:49:19,732 --> 00:49:20,961
- A lackey?
- What should I say?

1225
00:49:20,962 --> 00:49:22,231
- A lackey?
- How should I introduce you?

1226
00:49:22,232 --> 00:49:23,701
- You can call me a lackey.
- What can we be called?

1227
00:49:23,702 --> 00:49:24,871
Ms. Kim's lackey...

1228
00:49:24,872 --> 00:49:29,571
Kim Tae Ri's lackeys, Kangnam and Hyun Wook!

1229
00:49:29,572 --> 00:49:31,372
(Followers of Kim Tae Ri, Kangnam and Hyun Wook!)

1230
00:49:31,772 --> 00:49:33,042
Do whatever you want.

1231
00:49:33,312 --> 00:49:35,912
Are you okay with anything?

1232
00:49:36,012 --> 00:49:37,082
I like it.

1233
00:49:38,112 --> 00:49:39,851
(Crunch)

1234
00:49:39,852 --> 00:49:42,022
- I have a favor to ask you.
- Okay.

1235
00:49:42,122 --> 00:49:45,021
I want to ask Tae Ri for this favor.

1236
00:49:45,022 --> 00:49:46,722
- Okay.
- It's something important.

1237
00:49:49,422 --> 00:49:51,962
I felt bad about this all day.

1238
00:49:53,045 --> 00:49:54,975
I felt bad about this all day.

1239
00:49:57,075 --> 00:49:58,515
- It's about Dorothy.
- Okay.

1240
00:49:59,045 --> 00:50:01,015
I kept doing her ribbon today.

1241
00:50:01,385 --> 00:50:03,354
The ribbon was a mess,

1242
00:50:03,355 --> 00:50:04,714
and her hair was shooting up like this.

1243
00:50:04,715 --> 00:50:07,784
Kangnam, why didn't you tell me?

1244
00:50:07,785 --> 00:50:09,454
I felt bad while watching.

1245
00:50:09,455 --> 00:50:10,754
Why do you keep doing it yourself?

1246
00:50:10,755 --> 00:50:12,795
Because she comes to me to ask.

1247
00:50:13,965 --> 00:50:14,965
Teacher.

1248
00:50:16,195 --> 00:50:17,265
Do you need help?

1249
00:50:18,035 --> 00:50:20,704
(She picks on Kangnam for help.)

1250
00:50:20,705 --> 00:50:23,305
Do you like it best when North Pole Teacher helps you?

1251
00:50:23,705 --> 00:50:25,745
- Yes.
- Sure, because I do it the best.

1252
00:50:27,575 --> 00:50:28,615
Okay, it looks good.

1253
00:50:30,075 --> 00:50:32,045
(Eun Soo likes her hairdo.)

1254
00:50:32,185 --> 00:50:34,115
Teacher, help me.

1255
00:50:34,285 --> 00:50:35,714
We helped you a lot back then.

1256
00:50:35,715 --> 00:50:36,785
How pretty you look.

1257
00:50:36,985 --> 00:50:38,155
This time...

1258
00:50:38,255 --> 00:50:40,284
It suits you so well. Come on, let's go.

1259
00:50:40,285 --> 00:50:41,285
Doesn't she look great?

1260
00:50:41,385 --> 00:50:43,525
- Should I wear these?
- Yes, you should.

1261
00:50:45,625 --> 00:50:46,625
Here.

1262
00:50:46,725 --> 00:50:48,224
(He looks like a loving father of a daughter.)

1263
00:50:48,225 --> 00:50:49,265
I see.

1264
00:50:50,635 --> 00:50:52,534
(Taking care of all her details from head to toe)

1265
00:50:52,535 --> 00:50:55,305
Eun Soo looks super cute with the headband.

1266
00:50:56,675 --> 00:50:58,474
Do you want 1 or 2?

1267
00:50:58,475 --> 00:50:59,904
Just one.

1268
00:50:59,905 --> 00:51:01,045
Just one? Okay.

1269
00:51:01,915 --> 00:51:03,744
I thought Eun Soo liked it.

1270
00:51:03,745 --> 00:51:05,615
Me too, every day...

1271
00:51:05,745 --> 00:51:07,245
I feel so bad.

1272
00:51:07,685 --> 00:51:08,855
Please help her look nicer.

1273
00:51:09,085 --> 00:51:11,115
It's so cute. Seriously.

1274
00:51:13,925 --> 00:51:15,255
I'll go wash up.

1275
00:51:15,355 --> 00:51:16,355
Okay.

1276
00:51:21,025 --> 00:51:22,564
- Will you be okay tomorrow?
- What?

1277
00:51:22,565 --> 00:51:24,295
- Will you be okay tomorrow?
- Tomorrow?

1278
00:51:25,535 --> 00:51:28,404
I must have gotten something wrong.

1279
00:51:28,405 --> 00:51:29,475
About what?

1280
00:51:30,475 --> 00:51:31,475
What?

1281
00:51:32,205 --> 00:51:33,275
What is it? Is it too hard on you?

1282
00:51:33,575 --> 00:51:37,745
To me, it doesn't look like...

1283
00:51:37,845 --> 00:51:40,515
the kids are enjoying it.

1284
00:51:40,815 --> 00:51:41,815
The kids?

1285
00:51:41,885 --> 00:51:45,155
Yes. I still feel like...

1286
00:51:45,255 --> 00:51:46,855
they're a bit unenthusiastic.

1287
00:51:47,955 --> 00:51:52,025
I wonder if I missed something.

1288
00:51:54,765 --> 00:51:58,395
But you know, I was the same when I was young.

1289
00:51:58,665 --> 00:52:02,034
I acted uninterested on purpose.

1290
00:52:02,035 --> 00:52:03,035
(He acted differently from how he felt.)

1291
00:52:03,036 --> 00:52:04,074
This is the most important thing.

1292
00:52:04,075 --> 00:52:06,004
Let's say...

1293
00:52:06,005 --> 00:52:08,144
the kids don't want to do this like you say.

1294
00:52:08,145 --> 00:52:09,875
Then they wouldn't have cried yesterday.

1295
00:52:11,315 --> 00:52:14,484
Sure, they have a hard time focusing and they might lack enthusiasm.

1296
00:52:14,485 --> 00:52:16,485
But when I talk to them,

1297
00:52:16,615 --> 00:52:18,924
they really like doing this. They want to do it.

1298
00:52:18,925 --> 00:52:20,385
They just can't concentrate well.

1299
00:52:21,585 --> 00:52:22,725
It can't be helped.

1300
00:52:23,655 --> 00:52:25,794
But in their hearts,

1301
00:52:25,795 --> 00:52:27,564
they are enjoying this.

1302
00:52:27,565 --> 00:52:29,234
That was something we felt for sure.

1303
00:52:29,235 --> 00:52:30,734
- The kids made us realize that.
- Yes.

1304
00:52:30,735 --> 00:52:31,805
That's the point.

1305
00:52:32,305 --> 00:52:33,505
That's the biggest thing.

1306
00:52:33,705 --> 00:52:36,935
There is no reason for you to feel timid.

1307
00:52:37,475 --> 00:52:41,204
What is perfectly clear is...

1308
00:52:41,205 --> 00:52:43,045
Their tears are their answer.

1309
00:52:44,245 --> 00:52:46,384
Since we saw that,

1310
00:52:46,385 --> 00:52:47,545
we can be confident.

1311
00:52:49,415 --> 00:52:51,555
It's going to be okay. We got this.

1312
00:52:52,355 --> 00:52:53,425
I see.

1313
00:52:54,455 --> 00:52:56,724
Whenever I talk with Kangnam,

1314
00:52:56,725 --> 00:52:59,425
my heart feels at ease.

1315
00:52:59,825 --> 00:53:01,164
Can I call you my big brother?

1316
00:53:01,165 --> 00:53:03,695
Sure. Please talk casually to me. I forgot to tell you.

1317
00:53:03,835 --> 00:53:04,835
We can talk casually.

1318
00:53:05,265 --> 00:53:07,604
- Please be casual.
- Okay.

1319
00:53:07,605 --> 00:53:09,605
I forgot to tell you.

1320
00:53:11,135 --> 00:53:12,174
(Big brother)

1321
00:53:12,175 --> 00:53:13,504
(Where is my big brother?)

1322
00:53:13,505 --> 00:53:14,774
(Big brother)

1323
00:53:14,775 --> 00:53:15,974
You're the best.

1324
00:53:15,975 --> 00:53:19,315
(Being together means they can rely on each other.)

1325
00:53:20,245 --> 00:53:21,885
(My big brother is the best!)

1326
00:53:22,755 --> 00:53:23,955
You are like Toto.

1327
00:53:24,215 --> 00:53:25,385
Ready, go.

1328
00:53:26,255 --> 00:53:30,455
(Just having him around puts their hearts at ease.)

1329
00:53:33,225 --> 00:53:36,665
(In difficult moments,)

1330
00:53:37,565 --> 00:53:40,305
(he steps up in place of his little siblings.)

1331
00:53:41,005 --> 00:53:43,674
(Please listen to your teacher.)

1332
00:53:43,675 --> 00:53:47,705
Everything he said was comforting.

1333
00:53:47,945 --> 00:53:50,744
We were startled because we didn't know you would do so well.

1334
00:53:50,745 --> 00:53:52,115
(Thanks to joining of North Pole Teacher,)

1335
00:53:52,885 --> 00:53:54,984
(the classes turned more fun.)

1336
00:53:54,985 --> 00:53:57,954
He took care of many details...

1337
00:53:57,955 --> 00:53:59,824
I had overlooked.

1338
00:53:59,825 --> 00:54:02,025
I felt like I could rely on him.

1339
00:54:04,225 --> 00:54:06,225
(Let's figure out all the lines of movement tonight.)

1340
00:54:07,195 --> 00:54:09,364
(Sometimes, he turns into the eldest...)

1341
00:54:09,365 --> 00:54:11,535
(who leads the other teachers.)

1342
00:54:12,865 --> 00:54:15,775
(It's a given he will make the mood more cheerful.)

1343
00:54:16,035 --> 00:54:18,605
We have to pay a visit to the costume room.

1344
00:54:19,375 --> 00:54:21,845
(I will go to the costume room.)

1345
00:54:22,845 --> 00:54:25,075
(Even when no one was looking,)

1346
00:54:25,785 --> 00:54:28,245
(he stepped up and volunteered to do hard work.)

1347
00:54:29,385 --> 00:54:32,185
(He always put the other teachers first.)

1348
00:54:32,925 --> 00:54:35,185
- I think there is too much.
- Don't worry about it.

1349
00:54:37,095 --> 00:54:40,265
(North Pole Teacher is the sweetest.)

1350
00:54:43,795 --> 00:54:47,265
(Give it to me. I'll do it!)

1351
00:54:48,635 --> 00:54:50,405
(Costumes)

1352
00:54:50,705 --> 00:54:52,675
(Props)

1353
00:54:53,145 --> 00:54:54,604
(Consultant)

1354
00:54:54,605 --> 00:54:56,175
Ms. Kim, go rest a bit.

1355
00:54:57,175 --> 00:54:58,215
You might faint at this rate.

1356
00:54:59,045 --> 00:55:00,385
Go rest, okay?

1357
00:55:00,615 --> 00:55:01,745
Kangnam.

1358
00:55:02,115 --> 00:55:05,885
There were many moments I could only bear thanks to him.

1359
00:55:07,155 --> 00:55:09,054
When you first came,

1360
00:55:09,055 --> 00:55:11,054
it felt like I got an army to back me up.

1361
00:55:11,055 --> 00:55:12,264
- Really?
- She really needed...

1362
00:55:12,265 --> 00:55:15,464
(She really needed someone like you.)

1363
00:55:15,465 --> 00:55:19,635
If I ever get juniors of my own one day,

1364
00:55:20,105 --> 00:55:24,375
I hope to become someone like him.

1365
00:55:25,845 --> 00:55:27,074
"Let's go together!"

1366
00:55:27,075 --> 00:55:28,775
(And even to the kids...)

1367
00:55:30,215 --> 00:55:32,384
(North Pole Teacher is really good at being Dorothy.)

1368
00:55:32,385 --> 00:55:33,514
Thank you.

1369
00:55:33,515 --> 00:55:35,855
(Shy)

1370
00:55:37,155 --> 00:55:39,655
(Do Hyun also compliments North Pole Teacher.)

1371
00:55:40,655 --> 00:55:43,755
(I think you did very well.)

1372
00:55:44,355 --> 00:55:46,165
I'm quite moved.

1373
00:55:46,965 --> 00:55:48,465
Thank you for saying that.

1374
00:55:49,465 --> 00:55:51,865
(To the kids and to the teachers,)

1375
00:55:52,835 --> 00:55:55,834
(he is their moral support.)

1376
00:55:55,835 --> 00:55:56,835
Gosh.

1377
00:55:56,836 --> 00:55:59,505
(Sweet North Pole Teacher)

1378
00:56:00,805 --> 00:56:01,944
Okay.

1379
00:56:01,945 --> 00:56:03,815
(This moral support is getting ready to sleep.)

1380
00:56:05,545 --> 00:56:06,685
Aren't you going to sleep?

1381
00:56:08,585 --> 00:56:11,185
(Making a goodnight call)

1382
00:56:12,455 --> 00:56:13,555
Hang up.

1383
00:56:15,925 --> 00:56:18,595
(Hard-shelled softie)

1384
00:56:21,425 --> 00:56:22,465
Hang up the phone.

1385
00:56:27,205 --> 00:56:28,205
Hang up.

1386
00:56:31,605 --> 00:56:32,605
Did you hang up?

1387
00:56:33,205 --> 00:56:35,105
Did you hang up? You did.

1388
00:56:35,715 --> 00:56:37,645
You didn't use to hang up before.

1389
00:56:38,715 --> 00:56:39,845
I'm speechless.

1390
00:56:43,955 --> 00:56:47,725
(Goodnight, sweet man.)

1391
00:56:50,425 --> 00:56:53,925
(Ms. Kim is working late.)

1392
00:56:56,465 --> 00:56:59,635
(Reviewing the run-through video)

1393
00:56:59,865 --> 00:57:00,935
How adorable.

1394
00:57:04,335 --> 00:57:07,145
(Before the stage rehearsal...)

1395
00:57:09,315 --> 00:57:11,974
(To check before the rehearsal)

1396
00:57:11,975 --> 00:57:15,655
(Her checklist is extensive.)

1397
00:57:19,285 --> 00:57:22,425
(A sincere day has passed.)

1398
00:57:26,065 --> 00:57:30,265
(Day of stage rehearsal)

1399
00:57:38,075 --> 00:57:39,405
Is it 9:14am?

1400
00:57:47,645 --> 00:57:50,385
(Where is Hyun Wook?)

1401
00:57:51,515 --> 00:57:52,525
How romantic.

1402
00:57:53,325 --> 00:57:54,325
You're right.

1403
00:57:54,325 --> 00:57:55,325
(North Pole and Potato are already on a run.)

1404
00:57:56,155 --> 00:57:58,495
Our steps sound loud because we're heavy.

1405
00:57:58,965 --> 00:58:00,125
- Right?
- Yes.

1406
00:58:02,795 --> 00:58:04,665
- Should we push the speed to four?
- What?

1407
00:58:04,735 --> 00:58:06,535
- Should we speed up to four?
- How fast is that?

1408
00:58:08,765 --> 00:58:10,674
About this much.

1409
00:58:10,675 --> 00:58:12,004
- Okay, I'll follow you.
- Let's go at this speed.

1410
00:58:12,005 --> 00:58:13,175
Okay.

1411
00:58:17,515 --> 00:58:20,545
(The gap is getting wider.)

1412
00:58:22,255 --> 00:58:24,385
- I'm tired.
- It's tiring.

1413
00:58:24,885 --> 00:58:26,085
There's a car behind us.

1414
00:58:26,925 --> 00:58:31,994
(Excuse me.)

1415
00:58:31,995 --> 00:58:33,065
Please give us a ride.

1416
00:58:36,695 --> 00:58:39,865
(Tae Ri took a shower.)

1417
00:58:42,275 --> 00:58:44,905
(I want to show you our...)

1418
00:58:52,359 --> 00:58:54,989
(I want to show you our...)

1419
00:59:03,869 --> 00:59:06,938
(Our Seoul teacher is back.)

1420
00:59:06,939 --> 00:59:07,969
I'm here.

1421
00:59:08,439 --> 00:59:11,079
CO KUN, I'm happy to see you!

1422
00:59:11,209 --> 00:59:14,248
- Did I make a surprise visit?
- We missed you!

1423
00:59:14,249 --> 00:59:15,279
Yes.

1424
00:59:15,879 --> 00:59:16,879
(After finishing work on his music)

1425
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:18,049
I can't believe I'm back here.

1426
00:59:20,789 --> 00:59:23,659
(He returned while no one was around.)

1427
00:59:24,819 --> 00:59:27,589
(Barista KUN)

1428
00:59:28,829 --> 00:59:31,529
(He is busy the moment he arrives.)

1429
00:59:33,299 --> 00:59:35,169
(They did a mid-way update the day before his arrival.)

1430
00:59:35,569 --> 00:59:36,869
The crow sounds too?

1431
00:59:37,269 --> 00:59:39,338
Actually, the crow sound was the only one...

1432
00:59:39,339 --> 00:59:40,669
we couldn't record that day.

1433
00:59:42,069 --> 00:59:44,978
(Sending a fresh delivery that night)

1434
00:59:44,979 --> 00:59:46,249
Are you sure that's how crows sound?

1435
00:59:47,979 --> 00:59:48,979
(Cawing)

1436
00:59:49,479 --> 00:59:50,479
(Cawing)

1437
00:59:51,279 --> 00:59:52,489
(Cawing)

1438
00:59:54,189 --> 00:59:56,459
(He'll be finished after working on the crow sound.)

1439
01:00:03,899 --> 01:00:06,028
The crow has so much soul.

1440
01:00:06,029 --> 01:00:08,269
(Full of soul)

1441
01:00:10,499 --> 01:00:13,939
(North Pole and Potato are back.)

1442
01:00:16,409 --> 01:00:18,409
I ate an apple, and it was good.

1443
01:00:19,009 --> 01:00:20,049
It's definitely good.

1444
01:00:22,749 --> 01:00:24,278
- What is this?
- Who is it?

1445
01:00:24,279 --> 01:00:26,188
- Guys.
- Is it CO KUN?

1446
01:00:26,189 --> 01:00:27,249
What is this?

1447
01:00:27,349 --> 01:00:28,549
Who is it?

1448
01:00:29,559 --> 01:00:31,319
- What is this?
- Who is it?

1449
01:00:31,819 --> 01:00:33,729
- I came early.
- What is this?

1450
01:00:34,659 --> 01:00:36,858
- You came super early.
- I came early.

1451
01:00:36,859 --> 01:00:38,359
- What is this?
- I finished.

1452
01:00:38,399 --> 01:00:39,768
- Really?
- Really?

1453
01:00:39,769 --> 01:00:41,498
He was here when I returned from washing up.

1454
01:00:41,499 --> 01:00:43,299
We could have gone for a run together.

1455
01:00:43,739 --> 01:00:44,898
I'm so tired.

1456
01:00:44,899 --> 01:00:46,269
Did you go for a run again?

1457
01:00:47,139 --> 01:00:48,139
When was that?

1458
01:00:48,309 --> 01:00:49,608
- Camping?
- Two days ago.

1459
01:00:49,609 --> 01:00:51,279
Remember when we called you two days ago?

1460
01:00:51,709 --> 01:00:52,749
It was insane.

1461
01:00:52,779 --> 01:00:55,548
Did they actually cry?

1462
01:00:55,549 --> 01:00:58,149
I'd never seen anyone cry like that before.

1463
01:00:58,519 --> 01:00:59,719
Did they really cry?

1464
01:01:00,089 --> 01:01:01,988
And they look for Mr. CO KUN in every class.

1465
01:01:01,989 --> 01:01:02,989
Really?

1466
01:01:02,990 --> 01:01:04,258
- It's true, isn't it?
- Yes.

1467
01:01:04,259 --> 01:01:05,929
Is it because I gave them jellies?

1468
01:01:06,489 --> 01:01:08,088
(When is Mr. CO KUN coming?)

1469
01:01:08,089 --> 01:01:09,089
Ms. Kim.

1470
01:01:09,090 --> 01:01:11,929
(They asked for him desperately every day.)

1471
01:01:12,929 --> 01:01:15,098
(I miss Mr. CO KUN.)

1472
01:01:15,099 --> 01:01:16,198
Should I call him?

1473
01:01:16,199 --> 01:01:18,139
(While crying, they still looked for Mr. CO.)

1474
01:01:18,599 --> 01:01:21,609
While working on the finale number yesterday,

1475
01:01:22,109 --> 01:01:23,839
- I cried a little.
- Why?

1476
01:01:23,979 --> 01:01:25,239
Because it was so touching.

1477
01:01:27,049 --> 01:01:28,308
It'll make people cry, for sure.

1478
01:01:28,309 --> 01:01:29,418
- Really?
- Yes.

1479
01:01:29,419 --> 01:01:30,779
(Mr. CO cried too.)

1480
01:01:32,589 --> 01:01:35,789
(Meantime, Potato is in charge of breakfast.)

1481
01:01:37,519 --> 01:01:40,488
(For the ingredients, he puts as much as he can grab.)

1482
01:01:40,489 --> 01:01:42,229
This one is bigger, though.

1483
01:01:43,629 --> 01:01:46,028
(As for water,)

1484
01:01:46,029 --> 01:01:48,529
(he trusts how it feels on his fingertips.)

1485
01:01:49,129 --> 01:01:50,199
Add twice.

1486
01:01:50,839 --> 01:01:51,998
(Seasoning it roughly by his feel)

1487
01:01:51,999 --> 01:01:54,039
- But now...
- Hyun Wook's cooking skills...

1488
01:01:54,439 --> 01:01:56,308
must have improved so much since he came here.

1489
01:01:56,309 --> 01:01:58,078
- Yes, he has improved so much.
- Right?

1490
01:01:58,079 --> 01:02:00,209
He's been cooking dinner for us, right?

1491
01:02:03,449 --> 01:02:06,319
(Exploding after getting compliments)

1492
01:02:06,649 --> 01:02:09,149
At every great gukbap place, the pots always overflow like that.

1493
01:02:10,259 --> 01:02:11,619
But it's too... It's almost...

1494
01:02:12,189 --> 01:02:13,558
Half of it is gone, though.

1495
01:02:13,559 --> 01:02:14,628
Great gukbap places...

1496
01:02:14,629 --> 01:02:15,629
(He's become speechless.)

1497
01:02:15,630 --> 01:02:16,799
Is this okay?

1498
01:02:17,559 --> 01:02:19,869
- Is it supposed to do that?
- It is, actually.

1499
01:02:19,969 --> 01:02:20,998
- Really?
- So,

1500
01:02:20,999 --> 01:02:22,698
it's always dirty around here at good gukbap places.

1501
01:02:22,699 --> 01:02:23,699
- Really?
- Yes.

1502
01:02:23,700 --> 01:02:25,299
- But not as bad as this.
- I guess not.

1503
01:02:27,639 --> 01:02:29,879
Am I doing it right? I have no idea.

1504
01:02:32,139 --> 01:02:33,179
No.

1505
01:02:34,549 --> 01:02:35,918
But it's a little...

1506
01:02:35,919 --> 01:02:37,279
(The essence of flavors)

1507
01:02:39,019 --> 01:02:41,249
(Assisting him devotedly)

1508
01:02:43,019 --> 01:02:44,488
(Though it overflowed, it has all the ingredients.)

1509
01:02:44,489 --> 01:02:45,619
I think it's done.

1510
01:02:47,759 --> 01:02:49,529
Actually, it looks like the one from a good restaurant.

1511
01:02:49,959 --> 01:02:51,499
It does look legit.

1512
01:02:53,369 --> 01:02:54,498
Okay.

1513
01:02:54,499 --> 01:02:55,698
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

1514
01:02:55,699 --> 01:02:56,798
(It has the right vibe, but how will it taste?)

1515
01:02:56,799 --> 01:02:57,939
Thanks for the food.

1516
01:03:00,069 --> 01:03:01,339
Hey, it's so tasty.

1517
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:03,279
- Really?
- Really?

1518
01:03:03,509 --> 01:03:04,679
Yes. Try it.

1519
01:03:08,849 --> 01:03:10,849
- It's actually good.
- It's so good.

1520
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:14,448
It wasn't easy.

1521
01:03:14,449 --> 01:03:15,749
(He totally meant it.)

1522
01:03:16,059 --> 01:03:17,389
Hey, you can get married now.

1523
01:03:17,919 --> 01:03:19,119
But when?

1524
01:03:19,989 --> 01:03:21,059
I want to get married.

1525
01:03:23,929 --> 01:03:25,659
Are you going to stay until Tuesday, then?

1526
01:03:26,529 --> 01:03:28,199
But I have to leave briefly on Monday.

1527
01:03:28,529 --> 01:03:29,899
- To where?
- I have a schedule.

1528
01:03:30,199 --> 01:03:31,268
- Is that so?
- Really?

1529
01:03:31,269 --> 01:03:32,868
- To a broadcasting station?
- I'll come back after that.

1530
01:03:32,869 --> 01:03:34,938
(I'll come back after that.)

1531
01:03:34,939 --> 01:03:36,909
We need to hear the finale number.

1532
01:03:37,039 --> 01:03:38,608
- Do you want to hear it?
- Yes.

1533
01:03:38,609 --> 01:03:40,109
- Do you want to hear it quickly?
- Yes.

1534
01:03:41,509 --> 01:03:43,478
One, two, three.

1535
01:03:43,479 --> 01:03:44,718
Why do I sound like that?

1536
01:03:44,719 --> 01:03:46,049
(It starts with the voice of the North Pole Teacher.)

1537
01:03:48,149 --> 01:03:49,858
(Amazed)

1538
01:03:49,859 --> 01:03:50,889
Yes?

1539
01:03:52,659 --> 01:03:53,659
It's amazing.

1540
01:03:55,929 --> 01:03:57,358
(The singing voice of the children is added.)

1541
01:03:57,359 --> 01:03:58,359
I love it.

1542
01:04:00,699 --> 01:04:02,028
(The number that will be the finale of the play)

1543
01:04:02,029 --> 01:04:03,099
This part is...

1544
01:04:04,399 --> 01:04:06,568
- I liked how it was off beat.
- Yes.

1545
01:04:06,569 --> 01:04:07,609
Me too.

1546
01:04:09,679 --> 01:04:12,539
- This will be it.
- I love it.

1547
01:04:13,279 --> 01:04:15,148
- For today...
- It's moving.

1548
01:04:15,149 --> 01:04:17,048
- Right? It does move you.
- Of course.

1549
01:04:17,049 --> 01:04:18,418
(They only have rehearsals on stage left.)

1550
01:04:18,419 --> 01:04:20,248
- Today is...
- The rehearsal!

1551
01:04:20,249 --> 01:04:24,958
(Today is the rehearsal!)

1552
01:04:24,959 --> 01:04:26,929
- Exactly.
- We finally get to see the stage.

1553
01:04:27,129 --> 01:04:28,559
- I know.
- How will it look?

1554
01:04:28,959 --> 01:04:30,328
- How will the stage look?
- It must be awesome.

1555
01:04:30,329 --> 01:04:31,558
(Today, they're seeing the stage for the first time.)

1556
01:04:31,559 --> 01:04:34,398
I heard it hasn't been finished yet.

1557
01:04:34,399 --> 01:04:35,599
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1558
01:04:37,539 --> 01:04:39,339
First, it's big.

1559
01:04:40,309 --> 01:04:41,338
- Is that it?
- Goodness.

1560
01:04:41,339 --> 01:04:42,339
(Surprised)

1561
01:04:42,340 --> 01:04:43,409
It's huge.

1562
01:04:44,539 --> 01:04:46,649
- It feels so big.
- The venue is...

1563
01:04:46,749 --> 01:04:47,749
(Amazed)

1564
01:04:47,750 --> 01:04:49,918
- It's too big.
- What's going on?

1565
01:04:49,919 --> 01:04:52,249
It's way bigger than I thought.

1566
01:04:52,619 --> 01:04:54,519
I think it's bigger than the stage in "Open Concert."

1567
01:04:55,719 --> 01:04:57,958
(The stage of the school arts festival...)

1568
01:04:57,959 --> 01:04:59,359
(they've only imagined until now)

1569
01:05:01,159 --> 01:05:03,428
Is it going to be that huge? It's crazy.

1570
01:05:03,429 --> 01:05:04,659
(For the students at a small school...)

1571
01:05:05,129 --> 01:05:06,129
It's big.

1572
01:05:06,899 --> 01:05:08,669
It's so big.

1573
01:05:08,999 --> 01:05:10,768
Seriously. It's like a music show.

1574
01:05:10,769 --> 01:05:11,799
Look at the lake.

1575
01:05:14,409 --> 01:05:18,138
As for the stage, I only had rough ideas.

1576
01:05:18,139 --> 01:05:21,749
What I wrote while adapting the screenplay...

1577
01:05:22,379 --> 01:05:25,019
has come to life in reality.

1578
01:05:25,419 --> 01:05:28,019
I was very satisfied. Yes.

1579
01:05:29,089 --> 01:05:30,819
As for the waves,

1580
01:05:30,989 --> 01:05:35,259
they were created in a way I haven't imagined.

1581
01:05:35,929 --> 01:05:37,028
I loved it.

1582
01:05:37,029 --> 01:05:38,229
(Wicked Witch of the West can fall into the water now.)

1583
01:05:39,029 --> 01:05:40,969
- Now, I'm nervous.
- This is...

1584
01:05:42,169 --> 01:05:43,469
It's crazy.

1585
01:05:44,469 --> 01:05:46,439
- CO KUN, stand at the center.
- CO KUN.

1586
01:05:46,639 --> 01:05:48,708
At the center. The stage is huge, isn't it?

1587
01:05:48,709 --> 01:05:51,278
Okay. Show us the warmup.

1588
01:05:51,279 --> 01:05:52,408
- Dance.
- Nice.

1589
01:05:52,409 --> 01:05:54,309
(Dancing KUN)

1590
01:05:55,149 --> 01:05:56,618
We can totally rehearse.

1591
01:05:56,619 --> 01:05:58,149
- Does this open?
- It looks like the door opens.

1592
01:05:59,689 --> 01:06:00,689
(Dorothy KUN)

1593
01:06:00,690 --> 01:06:01,789
What do you think?

1594
01:06:02,049 --> 01:06:03,318
- It's really big.
- By the way,

1595
01:06:03,319 --> 01:06:04,959
it feels even bigger up here.

1596
01:06:05,189 --> 01:06:06,189
Is that so?

1597
01:06:06,190 --> 01:06:08,089
It's somewhat grand.

1598
01:06:08,489 --> 01:06:09,728
It's much bigger and cooler...

1599
01:06:09,729 --> 01:06:10,959
- than I thought.
- Exactly.

1600
01:06:11,559 --> 01:06:13,529
Why don't we close the curtain?

1601
01:06:15,999 --> 01:06:17,568
("The curtain closes.")

1602
01:06:17,569 --> 01:06:20,539
(What they've said until now is actually happening.)

1603
01:06:21,639 --> 01:06:23,538
Should we play the roles and run it through?

1604
01:06:23,539 --> 01:06:26,078
- Yes.
- Hyun Wook and I will do it.

1605
01:06:26,079 --> 01:06:27,478
I'll play Dorothy here.

1606
01:06:27,479 --> 01:06:29,919
- And I'll do what I can up here.
- Yes.

1607
01:06:30,049 --> 01:06:31,478
In that case,

1608
01:06:31,479 --> 01:06:33,719
please wait behind the door.

1609
01:06:33,949 --> 01:06:37,219
The wind is too strong, so the curtain is...

1610
01:06:37,959 --> 01:06:40,989
I think everything on the back is flying around too.

1611
01:06:41,129 --> 01:06:42,259
- Really?
- Yes.

1612
01:06:43,129 --> 01:06:46,528
Our staff is quietly saying, "Please save us."

1613
01:06:46,529 --> 01:06:47,529
- Really?
- Yes.

1614
01:06:47,530 --> 01:06:49,068
It's very heavy.

1615
01:06:49,069 --> 01:06:50,439
This is heavy.

1616
01:06:50,939 --> 01:06:51,998
Let's do it quickly.

1617
01:06:51,999 --> 01:06:55,438
Should we try it from start to finish?

1618
01:06:55,439 --> 01:06:57,809
- Yes, let's do that.
- Let's see what we're missing.

1619
01:06:57,979 --> 01:06:59,748
Narrator, please say the last line...

1620
01:06:59,749 --> 01:07:01,179
about the strange and wondrous Land.

1621
01:07:01,309 --> 01:07:05,319
Dorothy ended up in the strange and wondrous Land of Oz.

1622
01:07:05,849 --> 01:07:07,188
The sound of the tornado.

1623
01:07:07,189 --> 01:07:09,148
(Mr. CO's job: Playing the sound effect at the right time)

1624
01:07:09,149 --> 01:07:10,519
The curtain opens.

1625
01:07:11,959 --> 01:07:15,489
(Number 1, Dorothy's scene)

1626
01:07:17,159 --> 01:07:19,898
After a squeaky sound, Dorothy comes in.

1627
01:07:19,899 --> 01:07:22,629
(Dorothy enters with the sound of the opening door.)

1628
01:07:23,039 --> 01:07:24,199
Please say the lines.

1629
01:07:24,499 --> 01:07:26,268
Let's go together.

1630
01:07:26,269 --> 01:07:27,508
(Dorothy and Toto embark on a journey.)

1631
01:07:27,509 --> 01:07:29,979
The music will play. Start now.

1632
01:07:30,709 --> 01:07:32,738
With the bright music, exit that way.

1633
01:07:32,739 --> 01:07:34,478
Yes. Exit that way.

1634
01:07:34,479 --> 01:07:35,609
(They exit with the song for the road.)

1635
01:07:35,949 --> 01:07:38,418
The curtain will close when they pass the arrow marks.

1636
01:07:38,419 --> 01:07:39,789
(After Dorothy and Toto exit,)

1637
01:07:41,089 --> 01:07:43,158
Now, the Scarecrow's platform comes in.

1638
01:07:43,159 --> 01:07:44,288
(Getting ready for Scarecrow's scene)

1639
01:07:44,289 --> 01:07:45,319
Okay.

1640
01:07:47,029 --> 01:07:48,828
(Potato Teacher's job: Setting up the Scarecrow's platform)

1641
01:07:48,829 --> 01:07:50,999
Scarecrow will stand on the platform.

1642
01:07:52,059 --> 01:07:54,568
With the cawing of a crow, the curtain opens.

1643
01:07:54,569 --> 01:07:56,499
(Cawing)

1644
01:07:58,639 --> 01:07:59,708
Wonderful.

1645
01:07:59,709 --> 01:08:01,109
(Potato Teacher's job: Acting with the crow puppet)

1646
01:08:01,369 --> 01:08:04,139
The curtain closes while the actors stay on stage.

1647
01:08:05,039 --> 01:08:06,308
Let's go and find him!

1648
01:08:06,309 --> 01:08:07,778
(The group's signature pose)

1649
01:08:07,779 --> 01:08:08,949
The curtain closes.

1650
01:08:10,719 --> 01:08:12,619
And when the curtain closes, the narrator reads.

1651
01:08:13,519 --> 01:08:15,448
North Pole Teacher, you have to send Ju Eun...

1652
01:08:15,449 --> 01:08:18,589
to do the narration at the stage.

1653
01:08:19,019 --> 01:08:21,088
- Okay.
- Please check on her.

1654
01:08:21,089 --> 01:08:22,459
(North Pole Teacher's job: Getting Narrator Ju Eun ready)

1655
01:08:23,229 --> 01:08:24,528
(Playing the song for the Witch)

1656
01:08:24,529 --> 01:08:25,759
You wear the hat now.

1657
01:08:28,599 --> 01:08:29,938
When the music plays...

1658
01:08:29,939 --> 01:08:30,968
(When the narrator becomes the Witch...)

1659
01:08:30,969 --> 01:08:32,638
Wear the hat and read the line.

1660
01:08:32,639 --> 01:08:35,568
"What will happen to Dorothy and her friends?"

1661
01:08:35,569 --> 01:08:36,739
The curtain opens.

1662
01:08:37,179 --> 01:08:38,279
The curtain rises.

1663
01:08:38,809 --> 01:08:40,748
(Number 5, Wicked Witch of the West's scene, the kidnap)

1664
01:08:40,749 --> 01:08:42,379
The friends enter the stage.

1665
01:08:45,219 --> 01:08:48,048
The Witch grabs Dorothy's wrist and disappears.

1666
01:08:48,049 --> 01:08:49,219
Tin Man screams,

1667
01:08:49,519 --> 01:08:52,858
"Dorothy!" And the curtain closes.

1668
01:08:52,859 --> 01:08:53,889
The curtain closes.

1669
01:08:54,929 --> 01:08:57,599
The actors will stay on the stage...

1670
01:08:58,759 --> 01:09:00,668
and leave stage right.

1671
01:09:00,669 --> 01:09:02,098
Hyun Wook, you have to guide them.

1672
01:09:02,099 --> 01:09:03,799
(Potato Teacher's job: Taking care of the exited actors)

1673
01:09:04,199 --> 01:09:06,169
And set up the lake.

1674
01:09:06,539 --> 01:09:07,609
The lake.

1675
01:09:08,169 --> 01:09:10,308
Ju Eun and Eun Soo have to enter the stage.

1676
01:09:10,309 --> 01:09:11,339
(Where's the lake?)

1677
01:09:12,839 --> 01:09:15,649
(While the curtain is closed...)

1678
01:09:17,049 --> 01:09:19,988
Please check how many seconds you need to set it up.

1679
01:09:19,989 --> 01:09:21,089
Please come a bit forward.

1680
01:09:21,789 --> 01:09:22,819
That's right.

1681
01:09:24,359 --> 01:09:27,388
(The song for the Witch has ended.)

1682
01:09:27,389 --> 01:09:29,559
Things like this take time.

1683
01:09:33,069 --> 01:09:34,198
We have to match their pace...

1684
01:09:34,199 --> 01:09:35,328
- with the song.
- That's right.

1685
01:09:35,329 --> 01:09:37,438
I should play the four-minute one from the beginning.

1686
01:09:37,439 --> 01:09:38,569
Okay.

1687
01:09:39,499 --> 01:09:43,379
Okay. When you're all ready, the curtain should rise.

1688
01:09:44,439 --> 01:09:45,878
(Number 5, Wicked Witch of the West's scene, the rescue)

1689
01:09:45,879 --> 01:09:48,249
The music fades down, and Cowardly Lion enters.

1690
01:09:49,579 --> 01:09:52,048
(Playing Cowardly Lion)

1691
01:09:52,049 --> 01:09:54,289
Now, Cowardly Lion, try jumping over it.

1692
01:09:54,419 --> 01:09:55,649
Jump over it.

1693
01:09:57,859 --> 01:10:01,658
Ju Eun goes to the waves, the one behind the front one.

1694
01:10:01,659 --> 01:10:02,828
(Falling in between the waves)

1695
01:10:02,829 --> 01:10:04,229
"Water is my weakness."

1696
01:10:05,999 --> 01:10:08,699
"Thank you, Lion." And the music plays.

1697
01:10:09,069 --> 01:10:10,099
Go.

1698
01:10:10,569 --> 01:10:13,509
(Mr. CO's job: Playing the chorus number)

1699
01:10:15,169 --> 01:10:16,779
The music ends.

1700
01:10:18,839 --> 01:10:20,548
(With courage, the Lion...)

1701
01:10:20,549 --> 01:10:22,278
(Mumbling)

1702
01:10:22,279 --> 01:10:23,419
The music has ended.

1703
01:10:24,079 --> 01:10:25,278
Draw the curtain.

1704
01:10:25,279 --> 01:10:27,518
Draw the curtain when the music ends.

1705
01:10:27,519 --> 01:10:29,149
(The curtain closes when the chorus number is over.)

1706
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:31,758
(Yelling)

1707
01:10:31,759 --> 01:10:33,259
Good job.

1708
01:10:34,089 --> 01:10:35,359
(Yelling)

1709
01:10:36,529 --> 01:10:38,098
(It automatically makes CO KUN laugh.)

1710
01:10:38,099 --> 01:10:39,199
And...

1711
01:10:40,469 --> 01:10:41,969
the curtain opens.

1712
01:10:42,369 --> 01:10:45,569
Ha Yun is on stage alone. The rest are offstage.

1713
01:10:47,209 --> 01:10:49,608
We have to focus here.

1714
01:10:49,609 --> 01:10:51,208
"Wizard of Oz!"

1715
01:10:51,209 --> 01:10:52,638
- "Open the door, please!" - Open the door, please!

1716
01:10:52,639 --> 01:10:53,708
At that moment,

1717
01:10:53,709 --> 01:10:55,378
Ha Yun should exit in advance.

1718
01:10:55,379 --> 01:10:56,418
(The Gatekeeper exits the stage before others.)

1719
01:10:56,419 --> 01:10:57,749
He has to exit before that, right?

1720
01:10:58,219 --> 01:10:59,718
He exits after giving out the glasses.

1721
01:10:59,719 --> 01:11:00,948
He can exit right after handing out the glasses.

1722
01:11:00,949 --> 01:11:02,189
- Yes.
- Okay.

1723
01:11:02,349 --> 01:11:03,558
He can exit right away.

1724
01:11:03,559 --> 01:11:06,188
You have to give him the wizard's hat and wand.

1725
01:11:06,189 --> 01:11:07,189
Okay.

1726
01:11:08,059 --> 01:11:09,059
Let's see how it goes today.

1727
01:11:09,060 --> 01:11:10,298
Yes. We have to see it by their sides.

1728
01:11:10,299 --> 01:11:11,828
Hey. It won't be easy for you and me.

1729
01:11:11,829 --> 01:11:13,399
- You're right. It's not easy.
- We'll get ready now.

1730
01:11:14,129 --> 01:11:16,699
Should we do it from the top? What time is it?

1731
01:11:17,599 --> 01:11:19,169
It's 12:53pm.

1732
01:11:19,339 --> 01:11:20,909
- When are they coming?
- At 1pm.

1733
01:11:21,139 --> 01:11:22,168
Then it won't work.

1734
01:11:22,169 --> 01:11:24,379
I think we can go through it with the students.

1735
01:11:24,579 --> 01:11:25,579
- Really?
- Yes.

1736
01:11:25,580 --> 01:11:27,208
- Really?
- Yes, let's do it with them.

1737
01:11:27,209 --> 01:11:29,919
The one in charge of the curtain, have you checked everything?

1738
01:11:30,749 --> 01:11:31,749
Yes.

1739
01:11:33,649 --> 01:11:36,188
I think Kangnam answered. Who answered it?

1740
01:11:36,189 --> 01:11:37,918
- Because of those sunglasses, - Right.

1741
01:11:37,919 --> 01:11:39,258
you look so weird.

1742
01:11:39,259 --> 01:11:40,559
I couldn't see a thing.

1743
01:11:42,559 --> 01:11:45,229
- It's hectic, isn't it?
- Yes. It's really hectic up there.

1744
01:11:46,229 --> 01:11:49,429
The children aren't the problem here. We are...

1745
01:11:49,999 --> 01:11:51,298
- Us?
- We have so much to do.

1746
01:11:51,299 --> 01:11:53,609
(The teachers pull themselves together.)

1747
01:11:55,509 --> 01:11:56,509
(The kids finally arrive.)

1748
01:11:56,510 --> 01:11:57,638
- Everyone!
- What?

1749
01:11:57,639 --> 01:11:59,438
- Hello.
- Hi.

1750
01:11:59,439 --> 01:12:01,078
(Happy)

1751
01:12:01,079 --> 01:12:02,448
- Goodness.
- Gosh.

1752
01:12:02,449 --> 01:12:05,118
- Our actors are here!
- Gosh.

1753
01:12:05,119 --> 01:12:08,618
They are entering the stage!

1754
01:12:08,619 --> 01:12:11,889
Gosh. You look awesome!

1755
01:12:11,989 --> 01:12:12,989
What do you think about the stage?

1756
01:12:13,089 --> 01:12:15,288
- I love it!
- Do you? It's huge, isn't it?

1757
01:12:15,289 --> 01:12:16,289
- Yes.
- Yes.

1758
01:12:16,290 --> 01:12:18,729
Shall we go up on the stage?

1759
01:12:19,099 --> 01:12:20,768
Please open the curtain.

1760
01:12:20,769 --> 01:12:22,498
- Yes. Please open the curtain.
- Gosh. It's cool.

1761
01:12:22,499 --> 01:12:23,499
Isn't it exciting?

1762
01:12:23,500 --> 01:12:25,199
(The children see the stage for the first time.)

1763
01:12:26,039 --> 01:12:27,138
(They found Dorothy's house.)

1764
01:12:27,139 --> 01:12:29,038
There's a house. Let's live there.

1765
01:12:29,039 --> 01:12:30,438
The house is so tiny!

1766
01:12:30,439 --> 01:12:31,708
- I'll live in there.
- No.

1767
01:12:31,709 --> 01:12:33,379
Everyone, why don't you go on stage?

1768
01:12:35,149 --> 01:12:36,719
Gosh. They're looking good.

1769
01:12:37,519 --> 01:12:39,718
Everyone, please stand in one line on stage.

1770
01:12:39,719 --> 01:12:42,789
Let's enter behind the silver shoes.

1771
01:12:44,319 --> 01:12:45,358
You can do it.

1772
01:12:45,359 --> 01:12:46,489
Now,

1773
01:12:47,189 --> 01:12:49,428
- we'll do the rehearsal.
- Okay.

1774
01:12:49,429 --> 01:12:51,098
There will be music and everything. Okay?

1775
01:12:51,099 --> 01:12:52,799
- No!
- Why?

1776
01:12:53,059 --> 01:12:54,598
- Did you answer him?
- I was...

1777
01:12:54,599 --> 01:12:55,798
- Everyone.
- Is this...

1778
01:12:55,799 --> 01:12:56,998
- how a parent feels?
- Exactly.

1779
01:12:56,999 --> 01:12:58,199
(Parent KUN saw the costumes for the first time.)

1780
01:12:59,069 --> 01:13:00,339
They looked awesome.

1781
01:13:00,439 --> 01:13:03,708
"They looked sharp, and they look like actors."

1782
01:13:03,709 --> 01:13:05,209
That was what I thought.

1783
01:13:05,579 --> 01:13:06,609
They looked cool.

1784
01:13:07,109 --> 01:13:10,319
Especially for the costume, Won Jin was the best.

1785
01:13:11,349 --> 01:13:13,019
Cowardly Lion dominated.

1786
01:13:13,489 --> 01:13:14,548
He was so adorable.

1787
01:13:14,549 --> 01:13:15,549
(Mr. CO's pick)

1788
01:13:15,749 --> 01:13:19,089
Mr. Kangnam will be there, and I will be here.

1789
01:13:19,559 --> 01:13:21,429
We will help you.

1790
01:13:21,529 --> 01:13:22,928
Just do it as we practiced.

1791
01:13:22,929 --> 01:13:24,258
It's the same as the gym. Okay?

1792
01:13:24,259 --> 01:13:25,629
- Okay.
- Let's try it.

1793
01:13:25,729 --> 01:13:27,298
Should we cheer first?

1794
01:13:27,299 --> 01:13:28,299
Yes.

1795
01:13:28,300 --> 01:13:29,668
Potato Teacher, please do it enthusiastically.

1796
01:13:29,669 --> 01:13:31,799
This time, we'll say, "Let's go."

1797
01:13:32,299 --> 01:13:33,869
And then, "To Oz!"

1798
01:13:33,969 --> 01:13:36,878
It's Oz from the "Wizard of Oz." Okay?

1799
01:13:36,879 --> 01:13:38,539
Sounds good. To Oz!

1800
01:13:38,639 --> 01:13:42,479
Okay. From today, we are...

1801
01:13:42,579 --> 01:13:44,178
one!

1802
01:13:44,179 --> 01:13:46,618
- We can do it.
- We can do it.

1803
01:13:46,619 --> 01:13:49,248
- Let's go. To Oz!
- Let's go. To Oz!

1804
01:13:49,249 --> 01:13:51,618
Let's go! Get ready.

1805
01:13:51,619 --> 01:13:53,118
The curtain will close.

1806
01:13:53,119 --> 01:13:55,558
Please go to your spots.

1807
01:13:55,559 --> 01:13:57,659
- Teachers, please help them.
- Okay.

1808
01:13:58,959 --> 01:14:01,499
Where's my car? My toy ride?

1809
01:14:01,969 --> 01:14:03,369
My toy ride!

1810
01:14:03,899 --> 01:14:05,699
This is mine. This is my ride.

1811
01:14:05,799 --> 01:14:07,268
This is mine.

1812
01:14:07,269 --> 01:14:08,669
(The toy ride is now the platform.)

1813
01:14:08,909 --> 01:14:10,908
I can do it.

1814
01:14:10,909 --> 01:14:12,239
- Okay? Do it louder.
- Okay.

1815
01:14:12,439 --> 01:14:13,449
Promise?

1816
01:14:13,679 --> 01:14:15,909
You tend to forget after a while. Keep it in mind, okay?

1817
01:14:16,109 --> 01:14:17,679
- Okay.
- Good luck.

1818
01:14:17,879 --> 01:14:21,419
Okay. Are you all ready on stage?

1819
01:14:21,919 --> 01:14:23,149
Yes, we're ready.

1820
01:14:23,919 --> 01:14:26,388
Okay. The actors are in their spots, aren't they?

1821
01:14:26,389 --> 01:14:28,158
We'll begin now, everyone.

1822
01:14:28,159 --> 01:14:29,159
(Dorothy and Toto are on standby.)

1823
01:14:30,159 --> 01:14:32,898
(Experience and be moved by "Curtain Up, Class!" offline.)

1824
01:14:32,899 --> 01:14:34,168
We'll try it now.

1825
01:14:34,169 --> 01:14:35,169
(Check tvN Joy's official social media for details.)

1826
01:14:35,399 --> 01:14:36,769
We'll begin now.

1827
01:14:37,369 --> 01:14:39,068
Okay. Let's do it.

1828
01:14:39,069 --> 01:14:40,308
(Everyone on stage holds their breath.)

1829
01:14:40,309 --> 01:14:41,309
Let's do this.

1830
01:14:41,909 --> 01:14:44,738
Okay. Get ready and enter.

1831
01:14:44,739 --> 01:14:47,379
(The children's rehearsal will begin.)

1832
01:14:48,809 --> 01:14:52,219
(The kids are on stage for the first time.)

1833
01:14:53,919 --> 01:14:56,289
(They're good.)

1834
01:14:57,059 --> 01:14:58,859
(The kids are perfect.)

1835
01:14:59,419 --> 01:15:01,259
(The teachers are making their final push.)

1836
01:15:01,859 --> 01:15:04,599
(1. Recharging them with courage)

1837
01:15:05,359 --> 01:15:08,529
(2. Revising the music)

1838
01:15:09,029 --> 01:15:11,639
(3. Inviting audience)

1839
01:15:12,399 --> 01:15:14,038
(How will the last phase...)

1840
01:15:14,039 --> 01:15:16,879
(of their journey toward the stage unfold?)

1841
01:15:18,110 --> 01:15:20,110
Dramaday.me
